@1553 = ~I fall in and out of love all the time, Fade.~
@1554 = ~I... I just wondered. Have you... ever been in love before?~
@1555 = ~Oh. Are... are you sure? I... only wanted to satisfy my own curiosity. It's nothing drastic.~
@1556 = ~Okay, now you've piqued my own curiosity. What is it?~
@1557 = ~You can satisfy your curiosity elsewhere, because I am no longer interested in you or what you have to say.~
@1558 = ~Well, I suppose it would depend on what you wanted to know.~
@1559 = ~Just, you know, curious.What were they like? If you don't mind me asking, of course... ~
@1560 = ~Of course I don't. She was my first real love, and her name was Calia. We were together for about a year. I was about 17.~
@1561 = ~No, of course I don't. I fell in love with one of the stable boys, called Jak. I was about 16 or 17, I suppose.~
@1562 = ~What was Kirsten like? She was great. I had the hugest crush on her, but it wasn't reciprocated. I worshipped the ground she walked on, but she never even noticed me.~
@1563 = ~Ahhhh, my first love. He may have been fat and furry, but I loved him all the same.~
@1564 = ~You haven't? That... surprises me, <CHARNAME>. I would have thought that you wouldn't have had any problems finding love.~
@1565 = ~Why not? It may come as a surprise to you, but I wasn't always this buff and bronzed demi-god you see before you today. I was actually very bookish, and the idea of talking to girls just terrified me.~
@1566 = ~Heh, I didn't say I had any problems in finding love, I've just never really felt anything other than lust for any of my partners.~
@1567 = ~I've never gone looking for love, so there's no reason why I have found it. I suppose I've always believed that when it happens, it happens.~
@1568 = ~Truly? What made you realize that?~
@1569 = ~Simple, really. I've come to have feelings for someone else, and they are far stronger than anything I have ever felt before, ergo I can't have been in love before.~
@1570 = ~Because I'm older and wiser now. For love to be real, it has to be reciprocated.~
@1571 = ~Because I was just a kid!~
@1572 = ~Oh, I'm sorry. I didn't mean to pry. Maybe I could ask you something else then? Something a little less personal?~
@1573 = ~Okay, as long as it *is* less personal.~
@1574 = ~Fade, I know your game. You'll just ask me the same thing again, but in a different way. So let me set it straight--I don't want to discuss such feelings with you, ever. Okay?~
@1575 = ~You do? How many times?~
@1576 = ~Three or four times a day, normally. Bar wenches, girls walking down the street, tough mercenary girls, all tooled up and ready to fight--I love them all!~
@1577 = ~Fade, I wasn't being serious! I've only ever been properly in love once before.~
@1578 = ~I'm joking, Fade! To be honest, I've never been in love before. Not properly, anyway.~
@1579 = ~(Her face falls, and then her tail twitches and her features stiffen) Fair enough. At least I know where I stand now.~
@1580 = ~What went wrong, then? Why did you break up?~
@1581 = ~She ran off with the blacksmith's son one day. Turns out she'd been seeing him behind my back. I was pretty devastated.~
@1582 = ~We just drifted apart after a while. Although at the time I loved her very much, I suppose it was inevitable that we would split up. We were very young.~
@1583 = ~I... err... ended it.~
@1584 = ~The stable... boy? I see. Were your feelings... reciprocated?~
@1585 = ~No. I don't think he knew I even existed. Well, not in that way, anyway, He married his childhood sweetheart not long before I left Candlekeep.~
@1586 = ~Yep. Many a happy afternoon was spent tumbling in the straw.~
@1587 = ~Errr... no. I don't think he would have appreciated my interest in him.~
@1588 = ~That's a shame. I hope she now realizes what she was missing.~
@1589 = ~I doubt she even remembers me! We were only seven, after all.~
@1590 = ~And why do you say that?~
@1591 = ~Well, considering she was one of my tutors, I really do doubt it.~
@1592 = ~I'm sorry... did you just say "fat and furry"?!~
@1593 = ~Yes. My first love was my pony, Misty. I loved him so much!~
@1594 = ~Well, you didn't specify *what* my first love had to be.~
@1595 = ~(laugh) I see! But you must have felt something for... someone, once? You can't still be terrified of girls!~
@1596 = ~No? Says who?~
@1597 = ~Heh, no, not anymore. To be fair, I've had my fair share of crushes, but nothing serious. (sigh) Nobody loves me... ~
@1598 = ~Women have always been these strange, alien creatures to me. I doubt I'll ever understand them, and they'll terrify me even when I'm an old man!~
@1599 = ~Well, at least you're honest. And... I suppose that's a sentiment I can relate to. But if you've never been in love, how do you know... when it happens?~
@1600 = ~Well, if it happens, I'll be sure to let you know.~
@1601 = ~Easy. Your palms sweat, you feel ever so slightly sick all the time, you find it hard to catch their eye without blushing and you find yourself wondering exactly what they look like under all that armo-- (cough)~
@1602 = ~I think you just... know. It's like an instinct.~
@1603 = ~Are you trying to tell me that you don't know what it feels like to be in love?~
@1604 = ~And... how will you know when it has happened?~
@1605 = ~I... see. So what are these... feelings like?~
@1606 = ~Well, your palms sweat, you feel ever so slightly sick all the time, you find it hard to catch their eye without blushing and you find yourself wondering exactly what they look like under all that armo-- (cough)~
@1607 = ~Yes, I suppose it does. Unrequited love can be very cruel, can't it?~
@1608 = ~You know what it feels like? To love someone who doesn't love you?~
@1609 = ~Yes, it can. I hope it never happens to me again.~
@1610 = ~Oh, I see! So it was nothing more than a schoolboy crush, then?~
@1611 = ~You seem relieved, Fade.~
@1612 = ~Yes. Since then, I've been too busy to fit anyone else into my life.~
@1613 = ~Oh, believe me, at the time I thought it was the big "L", but now I know different. I've come to have feelings for someone else, and they are far stronger than anything I have ever felt before, ergo I can't have been in love before.~
@1614 = ~Well... and this is just hypothetical, of course, I don't mean this to apply to you personally or anything... how do you know when you love someone? What does it... feel like?~
@1615 = ~"Hypothetically"? Fade, that's just as personal as the last question you asked me! Let me set it straight for you--I don't want to discuss such feelings with you, ever. Okay?~
@1616 = ~Hypothetically? Okay... well... your palms sweat, you feel ever so slightly sick all the time, you find it hard to catch their eye without blushing and you find yourself wondering exactly what they look like under all that armo-- (cough)~
@1617 = ~(grin) Oh, stop mucking about, jester! You know what I mean.~
@1618 = ~Okay, okay, I'll be serious. I've only ever been in love once before.~
@1619 = ~Alright. Seriously, I've never been in love before. Not properly, anyway.~
@1620 = ~Can I ask you about it? What were they like? If you don't mind, of course... ~
@1621 = ~That's awful. Has it put you off... finding love with anyone else?~
@1622 = ~What is this? Twenty Questions?~
@1623 = ~What? Put me off?~
@1624 = ~A bit. No one likes getting hurt, but you can't help who you fall in love with.~
@1625 = ~Or maybe that is just what happens when you've been with the same person for a long while. You just drift apart.~
@1626 = ~I don't think that's true, Fade. I firmly believe that once you've found that special person, you'll be with them forever.~
@1627 = ~Maybe so. And you might get run over by a runaway cart tomorrow. All the more reason to live life to the full!~
@1628 = ~That's a very negative attitude to true love, Fade.~
@1629 = ~You ended it? Why?~
@1630 = ~I got bored. Simple really. We were young, she wanted to settle down, and I wanted to travel. It was inevitable.~
@1631 = ~She... caught me out. I was cheating on her. I ended it before she could.~
@1632 = ~Oh. I suppose I hadn't even considered you the type who would, you know... ~
@1633 = ~Be interested in another man? Why not? Why cut yourself off from half the population, just because they are the same sex as you?~
@1634 = ~Why not, Fade?~
@1635 = ~Well, I'm not. Not normally, anyway. Jak was... special to me. He's the only bloke I've ever... felt that way about. I don't know why.~
@1636 = ~You... did? Oh. I suppose I hadn't even considered you the type who would, you know...~
@1637 = ~Ahhhh... I see. Although I hadn't even considered you the type who would, you know...~
@1638 = ~Only sev--what? (She looks confused, but then laughs) Stop mucking about, jester! You know what I mean. I'm not talking about childhood infatuations!~
@1639 = ~No? Only adult ones, then.~
@1640 = ~Okay, okay, a sensible answer. My first real love was a girl called Calia. We were together for about a year. I was about 17.~
@1641 = ~Okay. I suppose my first love was when I fell in love with one of the stable boys, called Jak. I was about 16 or 17, I suppose.~
@1642 = ~(blush) Oh, you know... nothing in particular... just that... ummm... ~
@1643 = ~Hmmm? Just that what, Fade?~
@1644 = ~It's okay, Fade. I shouldn't have put you on the spot like that.~
@1645 = ~Your tutor--what? (She looks confused, but then laughs) Stop mucking about, jester! You know what I mean. I'm not talking about childhood infatuations!~
@1646 = ~What? (She looks confused, but then laughs) Stop mucking about, jester! You know what I mean. I'm not talking about childhood infatuations!~
@1647 = ~(grin) Oh, come now, <CHARNAME>. After the way you've... behaved around me? You're not scared of girls!~
@1648 = ~Oh, that just means I'm not scared of you. (try to pinch her cheeks)~
@1649 = ~Okay, maybe not now, but I used to be. To be fair, I've had my fair share of crushes, but nothing serious. (sigh) Nobody loves me... ~
@1650 = ~I... I wouldn't say that, <CHARNAME>. (Her cheeks flush, and she bites her bottom lip as she hurries away)~
@1651 = ~(giggle) I'm sure you'll meet one who convinces you otherwise, <CHARNAME>.~
@1652 = ~I think I already may have done, but I'm not sure if she realizes it yet.~
@1653 = ~Oh? And what makes you say that?~
@1654 = ~I doubt that! But that won't stop me from loving her, all the same.~
@1655 = ~(She gives you a confused look) Uh... okay, <CHARNAME>. Whatever you say... ~
@1656 = ~Hmm. Maybe you could add the urge to be near them every second of the day, but as soon as you do get near them you end up prattling on about nonsense to them all the time, and being excruciatingly embarrassed by this, but unable to stop... ~
@1657 = ~Uh, yeah. You get the idea.~
@1658 = ~Why do you want to know anyway? Don't tell me you don't know what it's like to be in love.~
@1659 = ~Are you taking the piss, Fade?~
@1660 = ~So even if you'd never been taught, you would know what those feelings meant? You wouldn't be able to... mistake them, would you?~
@1661 = ~Well, I suppose you could. It depends. What kind of feelings are you talking about here?~
@1662 = ~What's wrong, Fade? Are you trying to tell me that you don't know what it's like to be in love?~
@1663 = ~I... I don't know. No one has ever explained how it's meant to feel. I could just have bad indigestion, for all I know. (grin)~
@1664 = ~I have heard many descriptions of how it feels to be in love, but "bad indigestion" isn't one! Although feeling slightly sick can be part of it, as can sweaty palms, finding it hard to catch their eye without blushing and finding yourself wondering exactly what they look like under all that armo--ahem!~
@1665 = ~So you think you're in love with someone? Can I... ask who that lucky individual is?~
@1666 = ~I'm not entirely sure. It depends entirely on whether the other person feels the same way. I... think they may do, but I can't be certain.~
@1667 = ~They do rather like to tease me, you know, and since I'm not really familiar with such... (shrug) Let's just say that I dearly hope they feel the same way, and leave it at that.~
@1668 = ~I suppose that depends on who you choose to give your heart to, doesn't it? (She gives you an odd smile before returning to her place in the formation)~
@1669 = ~Well... I suppose, in a way, I am. I wouldn't like to hear of anyone having to suffer through unrequited love. It can be very cruel.~
@1670 = ~So, you know what it feels like? To love someone who doesn't love you?~
@1671 = ~Yes, it can. Even though I was only young, I hope it never happens to me again.~
@1672 = ~No! Not at all. Like I said, I am merely curious. If you don't like it, I won't bother you anymore.~
@1673 = ~No, Fade. It's okay to be curious. I suppose I was put off the whole love thing for a while. It just seemed another thing I could do without in my life. But you can't help it when you do fall in love, nor who you fall for.~
@1674 = ~Fade, it's not that you're bothering me as such, it's just... it's like you're using me to analyse something. Is there something you want to tell me?~
@1675 = ~Well, being knocked back like that. Once bitten, twice shy and everything.~
@1676 = ~I suppose so. I was put off the whole love thing for a while; it just seemed another thing I could do without in my life. But you can't help it when you do fall in love, nor who you fall for.~
@1677 = ~What are you getting at? It's like you're using me to analyse something. Is there something you want to tell me?~
@1678 = ~Yes, shy. And... unable to get to the point.~
@1679 = ~(She offers you a strange half-smile) You do? Well, that's... comforting to know.~
@1680 = ~I suppose it is. Don't let anything hold you back, right? (She gives you an odd smile and returns to her place in the formation)~
@1681 = ~(shrug) I suppose I just need someone to prove me wrong then, don't I? (She gives you an oddly penetrating look and smiles)~
@1682 = ~You... cheated on her? Well, at least you're honest about it.~
@1683 = ~Fade, it's not something I'm particularly proud of, and I wouldn't do it again. I could never put someone I cared for through that again.~
@1684 = ~These things happen, Fade--fact of life. I never intended to hurt her, it just happened.~
@1685 = ~(sigh) Oh, I agree with you. It's just that I... I suppose I don't like the thought of *anyone* else sharing y-- (She stops and looks to you rather apprehensively, as if she has only just realized what she was about to say)~
@1686 = ~But I'm just prattling on now! I'll just... all right? (She gestures away from herself and offers you a strange half-smile)~
@1687 = ~Well, after... after the other day. You did kiss me.~
@1688 = ~I'm not attracted to people because of their gender, Fade. I never have been. Why cut yourself off from half the population, just because they are the same sex as you?~
@1689 = ~I did. And as I told you then, I don't regret it; not at all.~
@1690 = ~Yes, I did. I've been thinking a lot about that kiss. I should possibly have told you this before, Fade, but I'm not that interested in women. I like you a lot--just not in the way you probably want me to.~
@1691 = ~So, people of the female persuasion do get a look in with you? That's... good to know. It's nice to know that you have loved another, but I was a bit worried for a moment. I thought that maybe you'd only kissed me to... ~
@1692 = ~(shrug) Well, it doesn't matter now. (She gives you an odd smile and returns to her place in the party formation)~
@1693 = ~(grin) Possibly, depending on what they are and who they are with. (She offers you an odd smile and returns to her place in the party formation)~
@1694 = ~(blush) Because... because you're quite a... special person, <CHARNAME>. To a lot of people. And... to me.~
@1695 = ~(She laughs and bats your hands away from her face) You say that now, but just you wait! I can be ultimately scary when I want to be!~
@1696 = ~Although you can be pretty frightening yourself. And not just in the "Son of Bhaal" kind of way. Also in the "messing with people's feelings" kind of way, too.~
@1697 = ~Oh, I think she does, <CHARNAME>. I just think that she is worried about making an idiot of herself. And that she is worried that she may possibly be getting hold the wrong end of the stick. I... dearly hope she's right, though. I don't know how she would react if she found out she was wrong.~
@1698 = ~Because you deserve someone who does, <CHARNAME>. Someone to convince you that not all of us are terrifying, alien creatures. Someone... close to you.~
@1699 = ~So do I, <CHARNAME>. I just hope you're willing to give her a chance.~
@1700 = ~Good. And I'm absolutely positive that she'll do everything in her power to... help you get over your irrational fears. If you just give her a chance.~
@1701 = ~Get the idea? I think I understand it quite well by now. I... I never imagined, though, that I... that... Well, that it would feel so much like being sick!~
@1702 = ~(She flashes you a quick grin, though for some reason not quite meeting your eyes, and returns to her place in the party formation)~
@1703 = ~Of course not, <CHARNAME>! I understand too well what you're going through to tease you like that. Because I've... I... well... It feels a lot like being sick, don't you think?~
@1704 = ~Well... feelings. I don't have to draw you a picture, do I? Just that you feel close to someone, and you want to be with them all the time, and... and... Oh, now you're getting me mixed up, <CHARNAME>! I'll have to take a moment to sort all these thoughts out!~
@1705 = ~(She gives you a rather self-conscious smile, and hurries back to her place in the party formation)~
@1706 = ~Of course you can ask--but I'm not telling you! Not now, anyway. Maybe... maybe later, when I've worked up the courage to... And when I do, <CHARNAME>, I promise, you'll be... the first to know, all right?~
@1707 = ~No, that's true. You can't help it. I mean, I never imagined when I first joined your party that I would--would--~
@1708 = ~(She stops short, a distinct blush rising in her face) You know what, <CHARNAME>? I forgot what I was about to say! Adventuring does sap your memory, doesn't it? Come on, we'd better be on our way!~
@1709 = ~Something to tell you? Does it... does it really sound like that, <CHARNAME>? Then... I... well... then I must not be making very much sense, must I? Come on, we'd better be on our way before I start spouting gibberish!~
@1710 = ~Yes. That's... that's exactly how I feel, at times... ~
@1711 = ~(The two of you stand there in awkward silence for a while, until Fade flashes you a quick grin, though for some reason not quite meeting your eyes) Well, this isn't getting us anywhere, is it? Come on, we'd better get going.~
@1712 = ~Well, in that case, some good has come out of it, hasn't it? And... and I hope, too, that the next person who... who falls in love with you, won't have to go through that again.~
@1713 = ~"Just happened"? I hope that's not the excuse you're going to tell the next woman who gives her heart to you, <CHARNAME>. And in fact, I hope... I hope you won't ever *need* to tell her that excuse.~
@1714 = ~Oh. So it's... like that? This is... a bit much for me to wrap my mind around it now, <CHARNAME>. I mean, after all we've been through and all, I thought... Well, I'm glad you've set it straight now, at least. We're... still friends, of course. Right?~
@1715 = ~And I've told you that I... don't regret it either. I'm not sure how much it meant to you, but for me, I... Well, I suppose we'll have to sort this out someday, won't we?~
@1716 = ~No, it's okay. I kind of set myself up for that one, didn't I? You're quite a... special person, <CHARNAME>. To a lot of people. And... to me.~
@1717 = ~But if you did meet somebody worth loving, wouldn't you... make time for them? Not that I mean anything like... that I'm saying... it was... just a thought. After all, you never know, do you?~

//LT46
@1718 = ~(Creeping up behind you, she tucks something behind your ear and with a swift kiss and a decidedly girlish giggle, runs away again)~
@1719 = ~(run after her)~
@1720 = ~(reach for whatever it is she tucked behind your ear)~
@1721 = ~You're in a good mood!~
@1722 = ~(She looks over her shoulder and grins at you) Can't catch me!~
@1723 = ~You want to bet on that?~
@1724 = ~But I bet I won't have to. You'll come back!~
@1725 = ~(stop running and reach for whatever it is she tucked behind your ear)~
@1726 = ~(Reaching up, you pluck the little flower she has placed there. Bringing it to your nose, you find its perfume is sweet and pungent. Looking up again, you see Fade has stopped running and is looking at you expectantly)~
@1727 = ~You seem in a good mood. What's brought this on?~
@1728 = ~(gesture for her to come over to you)~
@1729 = ~(laugh) Why shouldn't I be? (She stops, turns around and runs straight for you, wrapping you in a hug) I've got you, haven't I?~
@1730 = ~(tweak her nose playfully) And I love you too!~
@1731 = ~You certainly have. You can have even more of me later, if you'd like.~
@1732 = ~Fade, not in front of everyone else!~
@1733 = ~(You keep running after her, and with a shriek of delight, she runs on. You catch her easily however, which you realize was her intention all along. She allows your bodies' momentum to spin her around, and then she lands rather heavily on you, a huge grin on her face) So, you caught me!~
@1734 = ~Yep, although it seems as if you have caught me now!~
@1735 = ~(shove her off you and pin her to the ground) I certainly did. Now what am I going to do with you?~
@1736 = ~Oooff! Fade, be careful!~
@1737 = ~Cheeky! (She then gives you a rather calculating look and runs straight at you, knocking you off your feet and landing rather heavily on you) Got you!~
@1738 = ~(grin) You most certainly have.~
@1739 = ~(shove her off you and pin her to the ground) Now I've caught *you*. What am I going to do with you?~
@1740 = ~(With a mischievous smirk, she shakes her head) Nope, you come here.~
@1741 = ~(grin) Oh, come here. You know you want to!~
@1742 = ~Okay, have it your way!~
@1743 = ~Fade, I'm not in the mood to play silly buggers now, not in front of everyone else.~
@1744 = ~You love my nose?~
@1745 = ~Of course I do!~
@1746 = ~You know what I mean!~
@1747 = ~Really? Is that a threat or a promise?~
@1748 = ~(hold her tightly against you) Oh, a most definite promise... ~
@1749 = ~Well, that depends on what you want to be "threatened" with, doesn't it?~
@1750 = ~Well, that kind of depends on you, doesn't it?~
@1751 = ~(She smiles and shakes her head) I'm sorry, <CHARNAME>. I get kind of carried away sometimes. I tend to forget you are not used to such... open displays. Maybe later then?~
@1752 = ~Maybe later... what?~
@1753 = ~Yes, later is better... when there's no one else around.~
@1754 = ~I'm sure I'll get used to it with time, just not all at once, okay?~
@1755 = ~(smirk) Now then... what to do with you?~
@1756 = ~Are you open to suggestions, or do you want to see what you come... up with?~
@1757 = ~Whatever you want, Mistress.~
@1758 = ~No! Let me go! (She starts to try to wriggle away from you, but soon gives up) Okay, so you have me. What are you going to do with me?~
@1759 = ~Well, I am open to suggestions, or you could just see what I come... up with.~
@1760 = ~(say nothing, just bend your head to kiss her)~
@1761 = ~Oh, I don't know. How about this? (kiss her soundly)~
@1762 = ~Oh, I'm sorry. I didn't hurt you, did I?~
@1763 = ~(shove her off you and pin her to the ground) Ah ha! That ploy always works. Now I have you!~
@1764 = ~No, but I'm not used to being cannoned into by pretty girls. Let's save the rough-housing until later when there's no one else around, okay?~
@1765 = ~No, it's okay. I'm just not in the mood to play silly buggers now, not in front of everyone else.~
@1766 = ~Really? What else do you love, then?~
@1767 = ~Well, I may have to save that for later, when we have a little less... company, if you get my meaning.~
@1768 = ~(grin and bury your head in her cleavage)~
@1769 = ~(laugh) Okay, yes I do. And I love you too, <CHARNAME>, with all my heart. (She kisses you soundly)~
@1770 = ~(Her eyes widen) Oh! I... see. Gosh! (She looks down, then looks back up at you) Yes, I would say that was a definite promise... ~
@1771 = ~(She purses her lips and gives you a slightly quirky look) I'm sure you can think of something. I'm sure you have some kind of…tool at your disposal.~
@1772 = ~(grin) Oooh, I get a choice, do I? Well, in that case, you can promise to... threaten me later, okay? (wink)~
@1773 = ~I think I can leave that up to you, <CHARNAME>. Surprise me, okay? (She winks and saunters off)~
@1774 = ~Okay, <CHARNAME>. Until later... (She blows you a kiss and saunters off)~
@1775 = ~(She smiles and kisses you on the cheek) Okay, <CHARNAME>. It isn't a problem.~
@1776 = ~You're a naughty, naughty thing, <CHARNAME>. You do realize that, don't you?~
@1777 = ~You think this is naughty? Just wait until later, then.~
@1778 = ~And you are a filthy little minx for understanding, do *you* realize that?~
@1779 = ~So the choice is mine? Hmmmm... I'll have to think on this and... come back to you later.~
@1780 = ~(She grins lasciviously and for a fleeting moment you wonder whether it was wise to let a part Tan'ari with a broad imagination have such a choice)~
@1781 = ~(Just as your lips meet, you stop short and lightly trace your tongue around her lips. She shivers and her eyes widen) <CHARNAME>! Where on Faerun did you learn to do that?~
@1782 = ~Why? Don't you like it?~
@1783 = ~Just a little... trick I picked up. Works on all kinds of lips. (grin)~
@1784 = ~(She responds eagerly, and when you break apart, she is looking decidedly flushed) You've got to stop doing that, you know. As I've told you before, you really are going to get yourself into some serious trouble one of these days... ~
@1785 = ~Hmmm... I think I do, <CHARNAME>, I think I do.~
@1786 = ~Get out of there, you dreadful thing! They aren't just there for your entertainment! (She shakes her head and sighs as you bury your face deeper) Men... I ask you... ~
@1787 = ~(grin) With bated breath, <CHARNAME>.~
@1788 = ~(She tries to look innocent, but fails miserably) Me? A filthy little minx? (grin) Most definitely, <CHARNAME>... ~
@1789 = ~Err, quite the opposite, actually... Do it again... ~
@1790 = ~(Her eyes widen, as does her grin) Really? Well, that's something to look forward to. (wink)~

//LT48
@1791 = ~<CHARNAME>, love is a funny thing, isn't it?~
@1792 = ~Yes, I suppose it is.~
@1793 = ~(grin) Makes me laugh all the time.~
@1794 = ~Fade, you're not over-analysing things again, are you?~
@1795 = ~There seem to be all these unwritten rules to it, but no guidelines to what those rules actually are.~
@1796 = ~What are you getting at?~
@1797 = ~Well, I suppose the main guideline is, if it makes both of you feel good, and you're not hurting anyone else, why not?~
@1798 = ~Fade, no one knows what those rules are. We all have to find out the hard way. We don't seem to be doing too bad for a couple of rank amateurs, though.~
@1799 = ~(laugh) Jester! But there again, that's one of main things I love about you; you make me laugh.~
@1800 = ~But that's not what I meant. What I meant is that there seem to be all these unwritten rules to it, but no guidelines to what those rules actually are.~
@1801 = ~Yes, I know... I'm doing it again. But I can't help it. Everything I'm experiencing at the moment... it's all so new to me. I've literally *never* felt like this before. I'm still waiting to wake up, and to find out that none of this has happened, that it was all a dream. Everything is just so... different now.~
