@1803 = ~I know, it can be a bit daunting sometimes. But you just have to go with the flow. There's no point in dissecting everything in the hope it'll miraculously make sense.~
@1804 = ~(pinch her very lightly) See? Not a dream.~
@1805 = ~We're all experiencing new things all the time, Fade. Just think of this along the same lines, and you'll be fine.~
@1806 = ~(shrug) Well, before we admitted our feelings, we were just friends, and that followed a different set of rules. Now things have changed quite a lot.~
@1807 = ~I used to hide my feelings for you, for fear that you wouldn't want me, that you wouldn't feel the same way. Now I can shout my feelings from the top of the highest peak, if I wanted to! It's a... strange feeling, <CHARNAME>.~
@1808 = ~I know, but it's not just you. I'm having exactly the same feelings, Fade. It's completely natural.~
@1809 = ~You feared that I wouldn't want you? What isn't there to want? (lean in a little closer to her)~
@1810 = ~So just go with your gut instinct, is that what you're saying? But what happens if you have a... conflict, within yourself? What if you don't honestly know what's right?~
@1811 = ~Fade, you're over-analyzing things again. Just relax!~
@1812 = ~What exactly are you getting at, my love?~
@1813 = ~Look, I'll show you what's right, okay?  (kiss her gently)~
@1814 = ~You have a conflict? What do you mean by that?~
@1815 = ~(grin) I suppose you're right there. Listen to me! You'd think that we were the only two people to ever have fallen in love.~
@1816 = ~But I feel like I'm tied up in knots here... so many conflicting emotions. I don't understand it, <CHARNAME>. I try to let things take their natural course, but what if I end up doing something wrong?~
@1817 = ~Then I'll have to show you what's right, won't I?  (kiss her gently)~
@1818 = ~Well, you're not doing anything wrong at the moment, are you? And if you do, I'll be here to help steer you right. This is a partnership, Fade. We will enjoy the good times and work through the bad times together. It's what it's all about.~
@1819 = ~(She giggles in an oddly endearing way as you pinch her) Okay, I get your point. You're about as real as they get.~
@1820 = ~I could get realer, you know... (lean in a little closer to her)~
@1821 = ~(say nothing else, just kiss her gently)~
@1822 = ~And I'm not going anywhere. As long as we keep communicating, we'll be fine.~
@1823 = ~I know, but those experiences really only refer to me--if I make a mistake, I'm only hurting myself. Where you are concerned, I'm more likely to hurt you, and I don't want to do that.~
