@2008 = ~(The barkeep sends over a serving girl to your table. Fade leans back in your lap to get a good look at her. The serving girl smiles rather wearily at the two of you and asks you what you want. Fade grins at the girl in an alarmingly seductive manner) You're ver' pretty, y'know. I bets you gots thighs as soft as silk, haven't you... ~
@2009 = ~Fade!! There really is no need for that! (to the serving girl) Please ignore my friend. She really has no head for ale, and she didn't mean it, I'm sure.~
@2010 = ~(try to put your hand over Fade's mouth to shut her up) Please, just ignore her. I'll have a glass of wine, thank you.~
@2011 = ~(try to stifle a laugh) Fade! You can't speak to people like that, it's not very nice. (to the serving girl) I'll have whatever it is she's drinking.~
@2012 = ~(She giggles and covers her mouth with her hand, a rather endearingly girlish gesture) I can pay y'a complimenent if I wants to, <CHARNAME>. (She leans forward in your lap, wraps her arms around your neck and rests her head on your shoulder)~
@2013 = ~(After a short while, the barkeep sends over a serving girl, who smiles rather wearily at you both and asks you what you want. At this, Fade looks up at her) I'll be havin' of more of your lovelely ale.~
@2014 = ~(She leans closer to the serving girl, and mock-whispers at her) You're ver' pretty, y'know. But no matterer how pretty y'are, y' canna be havin' this one. (She leans forward again and clasps you to her breast) 'cos this one's mine!~
@2015 = ~(snuggle up against her cleavage with a self satisfied smile) I'll have what ever she's drinking.~
@2016 = ~(disentangle yourself from her) No, I'm not yours, Fade, not while you're drunk. Other times, maybe, but not now. I'm going to bed.~
@2017 = ~Suit y'self! But 'm goin' t'go an' get anotherlittledrinkie! (She gets up off your lap and wobbles away from you)~
@2018 = ~(She leaps up from your lap, holding the mug out of your reach) You want it? Come an' get it!~
@2019 = ~(She pokes her tongue out at you, and with a flick of her tail, runs back off to her new dwarven friends. You hear them cheer when she rejoins them, and decide that, even after all you've been through, you really don't want to face a group of drunken dwarves with an inebriated Fey'ri in tow!)~
@2020 = ~(She covers her mouth with her hand and tries to stifle a giggle) Oh, I'm a baaaad girl! I'm in troububble now... (the serving girl just shakes her head and leaves)~
@2021 = ~Oh, <CHARNAME>... jus' lightenen up a bit. (She takes a gulp from her mug) Thas' th'problem withpeoplelikeyou... don't know when 'm jokin' an' when 'm bein' sheriousus. 'm not jus' a pair of fantastictitsonlegsh, y'know... ~
@2022 = ~WHAT? Where did that one come from? What are you talking about?~
@2023 = ~(sigh) Whatever, Fade, whatever. I definitely think you've had enough of that now. (try to pluck the drink from her hand)~
@2024 = ~(As you place your hand over her mouth, you feel her grin, and as you are speaking, you feel her start licking and nibbling the inside of your hand. The serving girl just nods and leaves to get your order)~
@2025 = ~Ewww! Fade, don't do that. It's disgusting. I really do think you've had enough of that. (try to grab her ale mug)~
@2026 = ~(pull her closer to you) If you're going to do things like that, don't do them to my hand... ~
@2027 = ~(remove your hand from her mouth) Come on, Fade, stop messing around. I think it's time you said goodnight to all the nice people here and went to bed.~
@2028 = ~(Fade waggles her eyebrows suggestively at you and then wraps her arms around your neck) Am I a bad girl then, <CHARNAME>?~
@2029 = ~Oh yes, Fade. Very bad. In fact, I feel punishment may be in order... (lean forward and kiss her)~
@2030 = ~(disentangle yourself from her) Yes, you are, and I think you've had enough by now. I think you should go and say goodnight to all your new friends and go to bed, okay?~
@2031 = ~(She looks down at you and grins) You like it there? Wouldn'n't it betterer here? (She places her fingers under your chin to tilt your head up to her face)~
@2032 = ~Possibly... (lean forward and allow her to kiss you)~
@2033 = ~(disentangle yourself from her) Maybe, but I think you've had enough now and I think you should go and say goodnight to all your new friends and go to bed, okay?~
@2034 = ~(She leans back in your lap so her back is against the table and rests her ankles on your shoulders) It's jus' that peoples see that'm a part succubus an' they asss... asus... amus... think tha'm nothin' more'n a play thing for theirownpleasure.~
@2035 = ~(She sticks her finger in her ale and begins to play with the foam. After a few seconds, she with draws her finger and puts it in her mouth, seemingly oblivious to how suggestive this may seem to onlookers)~
@2036 = ~Fade, you're not doing much to counteract that image at the moment. Maybe you should just go and say goodnight to all the nice people and go to bed.~
@2037 = ~(She responds hungrily, and you feel her tail wrap itself around your leg. She shifts slightly forwards so that her entire body is pressed against yours. After a while your hear a drunken dwarven voice shout "Get a room, you two!" and lots of hearty laughter)~
@2038 = ~Want to take their advice?~
@2039 = ~(ignore them and continue to kiss her)~
@2040 = ~(After a while, you realize that she is flagging--her alcohol consumption is obviously catching up with her. As you break apart, she tries to stifle a yawn)~
@2041 = ~Come on. Maybe you should go to bed now.~
@2042 = ~(She gives you a slightly sly look and nods. You are almost suspicious at her compliance, but she stands up, bows and wishes everyone a rather slurred goodnight. Many of the patrons bid her goodnight back, and the dwarves begin to whoop, calling her "lightweight". She just grins at them, and takes you by the hand)~
@2043 = ~Okay then. But you're goin' to havta help me... ~
@2044 = ~No, Fade, you can find your own way up to bed. I'm not tired now. Go on.~
@2045 = ~Okay.~
@2046 = ~You push her in the direction of the stairs, and despite her sleepy protestations, she eventually begins to stumble her way up them. You decide to just leave her be.~
@2047 = ~(She nods and takes your hand)~
@2048 = ~(You get to your room, and as you fumble with the key, Fade begins to kiss the back of your neck, distracting you somewhat from the task at hand. Eventually you get the key turned in the lock, and both fall into the room together, Fade giggling as she lands on top of you)~
@2049 = ~(You both get up and stagger over to the bed, Fade because she is drunk, you because you are bearing most of her weight. She continues to kiss you for a while, and teases you by nibbling your shoulders and running her hand up your inner thigh)~
@2050 = ~(let her continue)~
@2051 = ~Fade, you're drunk. I'm not about to take advantage of that. Just lie down and rest.~
@2052 = ~(You end up in a mini wrestling match, and the drunk Fey'ri is no match for you. She just spends the entire time trying alternately to kiss and tickle you. As you begin to unlace her tunic, she yawns hugely, and her eyes begin to droop--you know that no matter what you do, she is going to fall into a trance)~
@2053 = ~(Shaking your head in amusement and, you have to admit to yourself, slight disappointment, you cover her up and crawl in beside her. She fidgets slightly, trying to get comfortable, and pulls your arm around her waist, so you are cuddled up against her back. You then close your eyes and decide now would be a good time to get some rest any way)~
@2054 = ~(She lies back on the bed in what could be considered a rather seductive pose, if her eyelids did not keep drooping closed. After a few seconds of struggling to remain awake, she finally gives in to her urge to trance)~

@2055 = ~(Fade shivers and looks around her a little apprehensively)~
@2056 = ~Are you all right... Mistress?~
@2057 = ~(ignore her)~
@2058 = ~(She nods, but does not smile) I am reminded too much of many things I do not wish to remember, here. This place reeks of the Abyss, of despair, of hatred and of greed. But I am fine.~
@2059 = ~(whisper) As long as you are sure. Just don't blow our cover, okay?~
@2060 = ~(whisper) What do you mean?~
@2061 = ~(whisper) Fade, I'm warning you, no silly outbursts. Just do as you're told for once. I cannot afford for our ruse to be uncovered. Do I make myself clear?~
@2062 = ~Come here... male. I need to speak with you.~
@2063 = ~Are you alright... Mistress?~
@2064 = ~Male? Who the hell are you calling "male"?~
@2065 = ~You presume to tell me how to behave in a place such as this?~
@2066 = ~(quietly) And I thought you trusted me. I will not betray you, Veldrin, by deed or by comment. It would mean both our deaths.~
@2067 = ~(whisper) I didn't mean to admonish you, Fade. It's just that you can get a bit, well, passionate about things you don't like. But you're right. I do trust you, and I know you won't betray our secret. Come on, we have much to do here.~
@2068 = ~(whisper) Exactly. That's why I need you to behave yourself. No silly outbursts; just do as you're told for once. I cannot afford for our ruse to be uncovered. Do I make myself clear?~
@2069 = ~(whisper) What do you mean about behaving in a place like this?~
@2070 = ~Not here. Order a room, where we can speak in private, away from watchful eyes and ears.~
@2071 = ~(She looks away from you, giving all the drow in the tavern an imperious, defiant look, as if daring them to comment)~
@2072 = ~I shall do that, Mistress.~
@2073 = ~But Mistress, maybe it would be better to tell me now, if it is so important... ~
@2074 = ~Perfectly. (She raises her voice slightly) Now get out of my sight.~
@2075 = ~(She glares at you, and you have no choice but to obey)~
@2076 = ~(hiss) Remember where we are! (loudly) Do as I say, male!~
@2077 = ~Yes... Mistress. (quietly) Are you alright?~
@2078 = ~I really need to speak with you, Veldrin. Order a room, where we can speak in private, away from watchful eyes and ears.~
@2079 = ~You dare question me? Then it is unimportant. (She raises her voice slightly) Now get out of my sight.~

@2080 = ~(When you enter the room, she quickly locks the door behind you, and then listens closely, obviously worried someone will be listening)~
@2081 = ~Fade, is that entirely necessary? I don't think anyone will disturb us.~
@2082 = ~So, what did you mean earlier?~
@2083 = ~I'm afraid it is. The drow are not unlike the Fey'ri... and the Fey'ri are a traitorous, paranoid lot. If any of the drow here suspects anything, anything at all, and they think it will benefit their house... (sigh) We are in real danger here, <CHARNAME>.~
@2084 = ~Thanks for pointing out the obvious, Fade. I had no idea. Now what did you mean earlier?~
@2085 = ~I know. The sooner we are out of here, the better, but we have to play along, just until we get the eggs. What did you mean earlier?~
@2086 = ~(She sits down on the bed, and you sit next to her) Once upon a time I would have relished being here. I might even have been tolerated... the Fey'ri and the drow have been known to co-operate in the past. Well, maybe not co-operate. I don't think that's a word either race totally understands. We would *use* each other.~
@2087 = ~(She picks absent-mindedly at the fringe of the blanket covering the bed) You know, neither the Fey'ri nor the drow have a word for "alliance". The nearest word in Abyssal loosely translates as "conspiracy", or "requirement".~
@2088 = ~It's the same with the drow. At least they have a word that roughly translates as "friend". We don't even have one of those. We have mate, supplicant, superior, inferior, slave... ~
@2089 = ~This place... it's too much like the Citadel. Its atmosphere, its inhabitants... the haughty, empty and cruel cast of that drow female's eyes... the hopeless, impotent anger in the male... it's all so familiar to me. Cruelty and gratification for their own sake... ~
@2090 = ~It's almost too much to bear! The temptation to raise the whip... to command... to lose oneself in the frenzy of physicality in whatever guise you seek it... I do not wish to go there again!~
@2091 = ~But my blood rebels... the fiendish side of me sits up and begs to be let loose here, even in this drow disguise. But to do that would be to lose myself again... to forget... to dishonour... ~
@2092 = ~You must help me, <CHARNAME>! I cannot lose myself... ~
@2093 = ~(wrap her in a hug) I will not allow it to happen, Fade. Together we will fight, okay? Be strong.~
@2094 = ~(wrap her in a hug) I didn't realise... I thought such a place would disgust you, but I guess I understand. You have to be strong, for both our sakes. I will try to help you in whatever way I can.~
@2095 = ~What are you on about, Fade?! You're tempted by this place? You're crazy, did you know that? Absolutely crazy! I should have left you back in Athkatla, with your Shadow Thief cronies. Just stay away from me from now on, okay?~
@2096 = ~Who said you would lose yourself? You gave up your heritage... maybe your blood is willing you to reclaim it. You should be proud of what you are, Fade, and embrace your more... demonic qualities. I can see you want to... I can see the fire there, in your eyes. (whisper) You can use me... ~
@2097 = ~(As you speak, she begins to caress the back of your neck, and then nibbles your shoulder, swinging one leg over you so she is sitting in your lap. Her intention is obvious)~
@2098 = ~(push her off roughly) Fade, what the hell are you playing at?!?~
@2099 = ~(disentangle yourself from her) Fade, no. This isn't you. Please? Not as drow. We'll only regret it.~
@2100 = ~(allow her to carry on)~
@2101 = ~(You storm out of the room, and the last thing you see before the door swings shut is the look of mingled pain, shock and despair on Fade's face)~
@2102 = ~(Her eyes darken, and she roughly pushes you back on the bed and straddles you, trapping your arms under her knees. She then pulls out a dagger and leans over you, running the dagger's blade slowly down your tunic, cutting through the laces)~
@2103 = ~(As your eyes meet hers, her former lustful visage is replaced by one of horror, and she sits up abruptly with a cry, releasing your arms, and flings the dagger away from her) No! I will NOT give in!~
@2104 = ~(scramble away from her) Are you crazy? Give in? What in the Nine Hells were you going to do then? I just thought that... that... ~
@2105 = ~(grab her wrists) Come on, Fade. You know you want to.~
@2106 = ~(Her eyes flare with momentary anger, and you wonder if she will attack you there and then for denying her. She then shakes her head, and when she speaks, her voice is dismayed and desperate)~
@2107 = ~I can't help it, <CHARNAME >! I'm sorry... This is why you have to help me. It's almost too much for me... I'm trying to resist, but it gnaws at me so... ~
@2108 = ~(She takes a deep breath and closes her eyes) I must be strong. You're right. But I can't do it alone... ~
@2109 = ~I said I'd help you, Fade, and I will. I'm sorry I pushed you. I didn't realise that your... compulsion was so strong. We'll stay here for now, so you can calm down. Everything will be better once you've rested.~
@2110 = ~Well, you're going to have to! You're crazy, did you know that? Absolutely crazy! I should have left you back in Athkatla, with your Shadow Thief cronies. Just stay away from me from now on, okay?~
@2111 = ~I'll help you, Fade, but I want it made quite plain that I have no intention of ever giving in to you. I don't know what instincts you are acting on at the moment, but I'm not interested, okay?~
@2112 = ~(Her eyes flare with momentary anger at being denied, but is soon replaced by a look of resignation) You're right, <CHARNAME >. (sigh) I probably would have ended up killing you if you let me carry on... I can't help it in this place.~
@2113 = ~I have to be strong, I have to fight it... but I can't do it alone, that much must be obvious to you now. Please, you have to help me.~
@2114 = ~I said I'd help you Fade, and I will. I didn't realise that your... compulsion was so strong. We'll stay here for now, so you can calm down. Everything will be better once you've rested. Trust me.~
@2115 = ~You would have killed me? Why?~
@2116 = ~(She begins to slowly unlace her tunic, but as her eyes meet yours, she stops and shakes her head, looking confused) No... this is wrong... wrong. Not as drow... ~
@2117 = ~What? No! Don't stop now!~
@2118 = ~You're right. Not as drow. We would only end up regretting it. I said I'd help you Fade, and I will. Come on, we'll rest here for now, so we can both calm down. It'll be better once we've rested, I'm sure of it.~
@2119 = ~You thought what? That you'd get a bit of gratification out of me, and that would be it? <CHARNAME >, I'm part succubus! You may not die if I kiss you, but if I let go... if I let that side of me take over... who knows what would happen?~
@2120 = ~This place isn't healthy for me! I don't know whether I want to mate with you or rip you into little bits!~
@2121 = ~You're crazy, did you know that? Absolutely crazy! I should have left you back in Athkatla, with your Shadow Thief cronies. Just stay away from me from now on, okay?~
@2122 = ~Is it that bad? Okay, I'll help you, even if it's just to stop you from ripping my heart out! Come on, we'll rest here for now, so we can both calm down. It'll be better once we've rested, I'm sure of it.~
@2123 = ~No!! You think this will be a simple act of gratification? <CHARNAME >, I'm part succubus! You may not die if I kiss you, but if I let go... if I let that side of me take over... who knows what would happen?~
@2124 = ~What? I didn't... Okay, I'll help you, even if it's just to stop you from ripping my heart out! Come on, we'll rest here for now, so we can both calm down. It'll be better once we've rested, I'm sure of it.~
@2125 = ~(keep hold of her wrists and pull her closer) I don't believe you, Fade.~
@2126 = ~Yes, rest... but keep yourself safe. I want you to promise... if I get out of hand, if I give in and become a danger... you will kill me. I can't live like that again.~
@2127 = ~Of course, Fade. But it will never come to that, trust me. Now rest.~
@2128 = ~Fade, I can't promise that. I can't kill you. I'll compromise, though. If it happens, and only if, I'll knock you out until we get back to the surface, okay? No arguing. Now rest.~
@2129 = ~(A look of dismay crosses her face) Yes, <CHARNAME >... I understand. (She turns away from you and lies on the bed, as if preparing to trance, and says nothing more)~
@2130 = ~(sigh) I'm part succubus, <CHARNAME >. You may not die if I kiss you, but if I let go... if I let that side of me take over... who knows what would happen?~
@2131 = ~This place isn't healthy for me. I don't know whether I want to mate with you or rip you into little bits! I'm possibly not... safe to be around at the moment.~
@2132 = ~(She wrenches her wrists from you and jumps off the bed) No... No! Everything... it's over, <CHARNAME>, possibly even before it began, but it's *over*! I can't believe you want me to become... to allow that side of me to prevail... just for your own pleasure?! Not that you would have been able to have handled me in any way!!~
@2133 = ~(She unlocks the door, wrenches it open and storms off)~

@2134 = ~(As you settle down, Fade sits on the end of your bed, her knees tucked up under her chin) <CHARNAME>, this isn't good.~
@2135 = ~Understatement of the year, Fade.~
@2136 = ~I know.~
@2137 = ~Fade, what are we going to do?~
@2138 = ~I know. (She pauses and seems to stare at the wall for a while) <CHARNAME>, does this predicament frighten you at all? Or is it just me?~
@2139 = ~You're... scared?~
@2140 = ~Yes, it does, and no, it isn't just you. Here we are, in the last place on all of Faerun we want to be... I'm sorry, Fade. I never meant to put you in such danger. I should never have taken you along with me.~
@2141 = ~This predicament worries me, Fade, but we just have to stay strong and work through it. Everything will be alright. It has to be.~
@2142 = ~"I know"? Is that all you're going to say? I don't know about you, <CHARNAME>, but this whole situation... worries me somewhat. Doesn't it worry you?~
@2143 = ~(She looks to you, and with a gentle smile, sits closer to you) We're going to work it out, that's what we're going to do. (She lays a hand on your shoulder) I'm worried too, but we will be okay. We have to be okay.~
@2144 = ~But how can you be so sure? Here we are, in the last place on all of Faerun we want to be... I'm sorry, Fade. I never meant to put you in such danger. I should never have taken you along with me.~
@2145 = ~Yes, you're right. It's just another challenge to face. We'll be fine.~
@2146 = ~Aren't you scared?~
@2147 = ~A bit. It's hard to stay optimistic down here in the dark, knowing that we are in possibly the most dangerous place on all Faerun.~
@2148 = ~(gesture her towards your open arms) Come here.~
@2149 = ~Just try to see it as another challenge to face, and we'll be fine.~
@2150 = ~<CHARNAME>, don't say that. Don't blame yourself--there was nothing you could have done to prevent this situation.~
@2151 = ~(She sits next to you, places an arm around your shoulders and rests her head atop yours) Everything will be okay. You look absolutely shattered. Just... try to rest. I'll stay here and watch for you, just in case.~
@2152 = ~Yes, you're right.~
@2153 = ~I really hope so, <CHARNAME>.~
@2154 = ~(She sits next to you, places an arm around your shoulders and rests her head atop yours) Everything will be okay--it has to be. You look absolutely shattered. Just... try to rest. I'll stay here and watch for you, just in case.~
@2155 = ~<CHARNAME>, don't say that. I wouldn't want to be anywhere else--because I'm with you. Please don't blame yourself. There was nothing you could have done to prevent this situation.~
@2156 = ~(She sits next to you, places an arm around your shoulders, kisses you and rests her head atop yours) Everything will be okay. Now you look absolutely shattered. Just... try to rest. I'll stay here and watch for you, just in case.~
@2157 = ~(She sits next to you, places an arm around your shoulders, kisses you and rests her head atop yours) Everything will be okay, because we are together. Now you look absolutely shattered. Just... try to rest. I'll stay here and watch for you, just in case.~
@2158 = ~(She sits next to you, places an arm around your shoulders, kisses you and rests her head atop yours) Everything will be okay--it has to be. You look absolutely shattered. Just... try to rest. I'll stay here and watch for you, just in case.~
@2159 = ~(She gives you a grateful smile and moves closer to you, nestling her head against your shoulder, wrapping her arms around you) I know everything will be okay--it has to be. You look absolutely shattered. Just... try to rest. I'll stay here and watch for you, just in case.~

@2160 = ~Cernd, has it ever occurred to you that nature can be a cruel mistress?~
@2161 = ~What makes you say that?~
@2162 = ~Well... I look around myself and everywhere I see bloodshed and death. I have always been led to believe that nature was the soft option... but now I'm not so sure.~
@2163 = ~(smile) Nature never takes the "soft option"... and we often learn that the hard way. We expect nature to be benevolent, but she knows the way of things. It's better to serve the balance and make sure what happens benefits all.~

@2164 = ~Fade, are you a planar creature?~
@2165 = ~No, I don't think so. (grin) Creature, maybe, but I hail from around here.~
@2166 = ~It is just that your aura is a trifle... strange. I know of your people, but you are somewhat of an enigma.~
@2167 = ~So it isn't just the tail and the talons, then?~
@2168 = ~No. I am used to those who walk so far from nature's path coming from strange and wondrous places, that is all.~
@2169 = ~I walk outside of nature? What do you mean?~
@2170 = ~Your place in nature's grand scheme is... uncertain.~
@2171 = ~So I'm unnatural?~
@2172 = ~No. (smile) Just different.~

@2173 = ~All the time you speak of the "balance" of things... yet how can you know what balances what?~
@2174 = ~What? Balance is important. To tip one's hand to far, whether in the name of "good" or "evil", will inevitably lead to chaos in nature. This cannot be.~
@2175 = ~But if nature is so powerful, surely she can prevent it herself?~
@2176 = ~Look at yourself, Fade. You are one who walks out of balance, yet you still exist. Nature will encompass you, but she cannot change you or make you walk her path.~
@2177 = ~I'm not sure whether I have just been insulted or not... but I take your point.~

@2178 = ~Jaheira, who was Khalid?~
@2179 = ~You dare speak his name--~
@2180 = ~No, Jaheira, I don't want any hostilities from you. I'm just curious.~
@2181 = ~I am sorry. My... protectiveness of him seems to follow him in death as it did in life. Khalid was... my husband.~
@2182 = ~I see. Then I am sincerely sorry for your loss--~
@2183 = ~I do not need your pity, Fade. Such sentiments do his memory no favours. You did not know him. Let us leave it at that.~

@2184 = ~Fade, Boo has been saying that you might be a... naughty thief. Please tell me this is not true!~
@2185 = ~Minsc--I'm a Shadow Thief! What did you think I was?~
@2186 = ~Maybe a cook... or a guard. I see you doing good, but Boo says you take things that do not belong to you, and that is not good.~
@2187 = ~Well... sometimes I do. But it's all in a good cause! I only take things from bad people... and the money goes to helping us on our, err, righteous mission.~
@2188 = ~See, Boo? No, do not tell tales! Fade is our friend, on the path to righteousness via the route of naughtiness! Minsc was right!~

@2189 = ~Minsc, what are you doing? Why are you... peering at my bottom?~
@2190 = ~Minsc and Boo were just wondering how it was attached.~
@2191 = ~What? How *what* is attached?~
@2192 = ~Your tail! Never has Minsc seen such a thing. Boo hasn't either. He has a tail, but it isn't long as yours. Do you buckle it on?~
@2193 = ~No! It's part of me!~
@2194 = ~Part... of you? But in Boo's experience, women do not have tails.~
@2195 = ~And Boo has had much experience of women, I take it?~
@2196 = ~We-ell, Boo has not told Minsc for sure, but Boo is very smart at getting into places no man or hamster has ever reached... so Minsc thinks, maybe!~

@2197 = ~(You wake up groggily after being mind-blasted by the illithid. As you pick yourself up and look to see if your companions are unharmed, your gaze rests on Fade. The Fey'ri is huddled in the corner, hugging her knees, her crimson eyes wide. She seems to be rocking slightly, muttering the same phrase over again in a guttural language you don't understand. You can only assume it is Abyssal)~
@2198 = ~(leave her be)~
@2199 = ~(stretch out your hand and touch her shoulder) Fade, are you all right?~
@2200 = ~(As your hand rests on her shoulder, she jumps, her eyes wild) Mind flayers! We've been captured by Mind flayers... Mind flayers... Mind flayers... ~
@2201 = ~Fade, calm down. We'll be okay.~
@2202 = ~Okay, Fade, you... err... have an insane moment in the corner, then. I'll be over... uh, there.~
@2203 = ~Okay? Okay?? You do know what mind flayers do, don't you? They turn you into slaves... into thralls... we're all going to be slaves!~
@2204 = ~Fade, pull yourself together! We are NOT going to be turned into thralls. We are NOT going to be slaves.~
@2205 = ~(pull her to you and hug her)~
@2206 = ~(She ignores you and continues to mutter to herself for a while. Suddenly she looks your way and whispers) I can't handle being a slave again, <CHARNAME>... I can't be a thrall!~
@2207 = ~(You cup her chin in your hand, making her look at you. You can feel her trembling through your hand--she is absolutely terrified) How can you be so sure?~
@2208 = ~Fade, I promise you, we will get out of this. You will never be a slave again, okay? I won't allow it. Please, try to calm down. Come on... breathe with me... ~
@2209 = ~Because I have no intention of letting my tale end here, Fade. So come on, now. I need you to be strong. Calm down and help me think about how we are going to get out of here.~
@2210 = ~(She accepts your embrace the same way a frightened child would--by clinging on to you as fiercely as she can. Her breathing is quick and shallow, and you can feel her heart thundering against her rib cage)~
@2211 = ~Please, Fade, try to calm down. We'll get out of this, I promise. You'll never have to be a slave again. Come on... breathe with me... ~
@2212 = ~(You feel her try to nod, and try to settle her breathing by imitating you. Her eyes never leave you face, and she seems to draw strength from your calm demeanor) Yes, we will be fine.~
@2213 = ~(She tries to smile, but it comes out as a twisted grimace. She is obviously still frightened, but you now know you will be able to count on her if necessary)~
@2214 = ~(She nods and sits down opposite you, studying your face, and she seems to draw strength from your calm demeanor) Yes, let us think about how we will get out.~

//LT54
@2215 = ~Can I ask you a silly question, <CHARNAME>?~
@2216 = ~Of course you can, my sweet. What is it?~
@2217 = ~(smile) That depends on just how silly it is, doesn't it?~
@2218 = ~Oh, Fade, not again. No, I don't know the one about the cleric, the rhinoceros and the vampire, nor do I know why clouds sometimes look like things, neither do I know why some people have, as you put it the other day, "funny looking heads"!~
@2219 = ~I just wanted to know... well... why did you agree to take me with you? You could easily have declined mine and Aran's offer. but you didn't.~
@2220 = ~I don't know. Seemed like a good idea at the time, I suppose.~
@2221 = ~Because you seemed so sincere in wanting to help me. I was wary of your intentions at first, but I've learnt to trust my instincts, and they were telling me to take you along.~
@2222 = ~Fade, why does it matter? All that matters is that I did take you, and I'm infinitely glad I did.~
@2223 = ~(grin) I thought you looked rather fine in all that black leather.~
@2224 = ~It's not too silly. I just wanted to know... well... why did you agree to take me with you? You could easily have declined mine and Aran's offer, but you didn't.~
@2225 = ~No! It's nothing like that... and what do you mean by that, anyway?!~
@2226 = ~Nothing. It's just that you can be a bit... random in what you talk about sometimes, that's all. So what did you want to know?~
@2227 = ~Well, you've got to admit it, Fade. You do talk utter nonsense sometimes!~
@2228 = ~I mean, unless it's important, don't bug me with it, okay?~
@2229 = ~Oh. That's all? Well... I suppose it's as good a reason as any.~
@2230 = ~What did you expect? I guessed you would be competent, and so I thought you could be useful. But that's all changed now.~
@2231 = ~Well, that and the fact that I thought you looked rather fine in all that black leather.~
@2232 = ~I admit, there were no thunderbolts when I first saw you. I was more worried that you might be a spy.. I had a job to do, and you offered to help me. That's it, I'm afraid.~
@2233 = ~Fade, when I first saw you, I thought you were the most beautiful creature I had ever seen. I was acutely aware that you were working for Aran, and I thought you were possibly his spy, but still I let you join us. And I'm glad I did.~
@2234 = ~Yes, I was very sincere. That surprised a few people. I had a bit of a reputation for being an "act first--think later" kind of person, but as soon as I found out what had happened, I knew I just had to help you. I'm glad I did.~
@2235 = ~As am I. I guessed you would be competent, and so I thought you could be useful. But that's all changed now.~
@2236 = ~(grin) Well, there was also the issue that I thought you looked mighty fine in all that black leather.~
@2237 = ~I thought I'd never admit this to anyone, much less you, but when I first saw you, I thought you were the most beautiful creature I had ever seen. I was acutely aware that you were working for Aran, and I thought you were possibly his spy, but still I let you join us. And I'm glad I did, too.~
@2238 = ~It matters because... well... I never intended any of this to happen. I joined you because I thought I could help you. But the more I think about it, the more it makes me wonder. You didn't have to take me along. You could have left me there, but you didn't.~
@2239 = ~What told you to take me along? What would have happened to me if you hadn't? Was it preordained? A fated meeting? Or merely a coincidence?~
@2240 = ~I believe we were fated to meet. I went with my instinct--I guessed you would be competent, but there was something else. I don't know what it was, but I just knew you had to come with me. And I'm glad you did.~
@2241 = ~It's just a coincidence, Fade. A happy one, but a coincidence, nothing more. I took you along because I thought you might be useful. Never did I think we would become this close. But we have, and that's what is important.~
@2242 = ~(grin) <CHARNAME>, I was trying to be serious!~
@2243 = ~I am being serious! When I first saw you, I thought you were the most beautiful creature I had ever seen. I was acutely aware that you were working for Aran, and I thought you were possibly his spy, but still I let you join us. And I'm glad I did, too.~
@2244 = ~(grin) Oh, come on, what was I supposed to do? A young lady, all clad in leather, offers me her services... I'm an impressionable young man, and that kind of thing *really* impresses me!~
@2245 = ~Nonsense?! I make informed and, ummm, knowledgeable remarks about my surroundings! (chuckle) Okay, I know I waffle on about rubbish sometimes, it's something that used to happen a lot in the Guild to pass the time when we were bored.~
@2246 = ~But this time I'm serious. Why did you agree to take me with you? You could easily have declined mine and Aran's s offer, but you didn't.~
@2247 = ~(sigh) <CHARNAME>, please don't be like that. This is important to me. I know that's not the same as important to the group, but there is something I would really like to ask you.~
@2248 = ~Yes, it has, hasn't it? You know, I never intended any of this to happen. I knew I wanted to help you--what happened to Imoen really struck a chord in me. I've been helping to try to stamp out the slave trade in Athkatla, but it's like trying to hold back the sea. As soon as we think we've stopped one route, another one pops up almost immediately.~
@2249 = ~I thought in helping you to rescue Imoen, another one so wrongfully incarcerated would be freed. I never once thought that the man I agreed to help would become so dear to me.~
@2250 = ~You've been helping the slaves escape? I bet Aran doesn't like that.~
@2251 = ~I will admit that when I first met you, I was very wary of you. But as I got to know you, I suppose it was inevitable that you would become dear to me too.~
@2252 = ~So, what did you think of me when we first met?~
@2253 = ~Not the answer I wanted to hear, but an honest one, and I thank you for that. I will admit, I never intended for any of this to happen either. I knew I wanted to help you--what happened to Imoen really struck a chord in me. I've been helping to try to stamp out the slave trade in Athkatla, but it's like trying to hold back the sea. As soon as we think we've stopped one route, another one pops up almost immediately.~
@2254 = ~(blush) Really? I... I never realized that. I thought I was just a burden to you.~
@2255 = ~You were never a burden to me. So, what did you think of me when we first met?~
@2256 = ~Why are you blushing? Hasn't anyone ever told you that you're beautiful before?~
@2257 = ~(grin) Oh, come on, what was I supposed to think? A young lady, all clad in leather, offers me her services... I'm an impressionable young man, and that kind of thing *really* impresses me!~
@2258 = ~Something told you? Well, I don't know what that would have been. I'm not big on Gods, nor fate. After everything that has happened to me, it seems absurd to put it down to either.~
@2259 = ~All I knew is that I wanted to help you--what happened to Imoen really struck a chord in me. I've been helping to try to stamp out the slave trade in Athkatla, but it's like trying to hold back the sea. As soon as we think we've stopped one route, another one pops up almost immediately.~
@2260 = ~Yes, it is, isn't it? You know, I never intended any of this to happen. I knew I wanted to help you--what happened to Imoen really struck a chord in me. I've been helping to try to stamp out the slave trade in Athkatla, but it's like trying to hold back the sea. As soon as we think we've stopped one route, another one pops up almost immediately.~
@2261 = ~(laugh) Oh, <CHARNAME>! If that's how you view women in black leather, you must have been is some kind of heaven in the Guild!~
@2262 = ~No, not really. You were the only one who affected me that way. Hasn't anyone ever told you that you're beautiful before?~
@2263 = ~Ahhh, I'm joking. I will admit that when I first met you, I was very wary of you. But as I got to know you, I suppose it was inevitable that you would become dear to me.~
@2264 = ~I suppose. What did you think of me when we first met?~
@2265 = ~Aran? He... doesn't know. At least I don't think he knows. He's never pulled me up for it. It's something I do when I get time to myself. I can't just sit there and watch people being used like that--I had to do something. Hence the reason I had to help you.~
@2266 = ~That's almost noble of you, Fade.~
@2267 = ~I see. So, what did you think of me when we first met?~
@2268 = ~Do you know the first thing that struck me about you? How... normal you are. I knew from the outset that you were a Bhaalspawn, and so I think I expected you to be... I don't know, a little larger-than-life, I suppose. But you're not.~
@2269 = ~And is that a bad thing?~
@2270 = ~I see. Were you disappointed?~
@2271 = ~I wasn't brought up to be a Bhaalspawn. I was brought up to be a normal person. A lot of people seem to expect me to be some kind of supernatural force, but I'm not.~
@2272 = ~The first thing that struck me about you was how... normal you were. I knew from the outset that you were a Bhaalspawn, and so I think I expected you to be... I don't know, a little larger-than-life, I suppose. But you're not.~
@2273 = ~No one who has ever counted, no. I hold no illusions about my... differences.~
@2274 = ~Your "differences", as you put them, are part of your charm, Fade. So, how about me? What did you think of me when we first met?~
@2275 = ~Okay, your "differences" did kind of trouble me for a while, but not now. I love you--all of you. So, how about me? What did you think of me when we first met?~
@2276 = ~Noble? Not really. Big paladins running around in shiny armour are noble, not larcenous petty thieves with a weakness for shiny things. I help because I don't like it--and I try to change things I don't like!~
@2277 = ~So, did you try to change me, then?~
@2278 = ~Okay, point taken. Well, I've spilled the beans--what about you? What did you think of me when we first met?~
@2279 = ~No, it isn't. I was expecting to be completely overwhelmed by you. Well, I suppose I was, in a way, just not in the way I was expecting.~
@2280 = ~You were? How?~
@2281 = ~The feeling is mutual. Once you'd been with us for a while, I didn't know what had hit me.~
@2282 = ~No, not at all. I... liked the fact that you were normal. I soon found myself being attracted to your strength--not your physical strength, but the way you seem to cope with things. You're so, well, dependable. I found that almost comforting.~
@2283 = ~Then you rescued me from Mallon. I knew then I was lost to you. I think I've been yours a lot longer than you realise... and possibly longer than I would care to admit.~
@2284 = ~And I for one am glad that you're not. I... liked the fact that you were normal. I soon found myself being attracted to your strength--not your physical strength, but the way you seem to cope with things. You're so, well, dependable. I found that almost comforting.~
@2285 = ~No, I didn't. I said I only like to change things I *don't* like... and I liked you from the outset. You are so strong--I don't mean your physical strength, but the way you cope with things. You're so, well, dependable. I found that almost comforting.~
@2286 = ~I... liked the fact that you were normal. What overwhelmed me was your strength--not your physical strength, but the way you seem to cope with things. I was overwhelmed by my own feelings for you.~
@2287 = ~(chuckle) If only we had been more honest with our feelings--it would have saved a lot of heartache and agonizing on my part, I can tell you! But I was overwhelmed by my feelings for you. You are so strong--I don't mean your physical strength, but the way you cope with things. You're so, well, dependable. I found that almost comforting.~

//LT56
@2288 = ~(The party has stopped for a short break and you sit for awhile around the fire discussing the day's events so far and what the future may hold. Slowly the others drift off to collect their things, leaving you and Fade alone)~
@2289 = ~(Though she participated in the discussions there has been a darkness about her that even the light of the fire could not push back. Even now she gazes into the fire with a solemn and troubled look, lost in her own thoughts)~
@2290 = ~Fade, what is it? What has you so troubled?~
@2291 = ~You wear the darkness about you like a cloak. Take it off for a bit, you're safe.~
@2292 = ~Keep that look much longer and it'll freeze on your face, and we wouldn't want that.~
@2293 = ~It's nothing really, <CHARNAME>. Just thinking.~
@2294 = ~I know you better than that. It isn't "nothing". Please, you know you can tell me.~
@2295 = ~Something is weighing heavily on you, honeykitten, I can tell. It might help to talk about it.~
@2296 = ~Okay. Don't say I didn't ask. Come on, we have to go.~
@2297 = ~Am I, <CHARNAME>? I'm not so sure.~
@2298 = ~What do you mean?~
@2299 = ~Of course you're safe. You're surrounded by friends and we've dealt with the slavers, if that's what you're worried about.~
@2300 = ~(wrap her in your arms but say nothing)~
@2301 = ~What? I'm sorry. I wasn't really concentrating. I was thinking of... other things.~
@2302 = ~I didn't mean to add to your troubles.~
@2303 = ~Other things? What other things?~
@2304 = ~Now that I've pulled your attention from the fire, what's wrong?~
@2305 = ~(sigh) Since we last spoke, I have been thinking about... my past, and I'm worried we haven't seen the last of the Pasha. There is no way he would give up this easily.~
@2306 = ~I bought your contract. He has no legal right to you anymore.~
@2307 = ~His men are dead. A rational man would cut his losses.~
@2308 = ~(gather her into a warm embrace) It's been on my mind too.~
@2309 = ~(groan) Why do you call me that? Okay, you're just trying to cheer me up. (smile) Thank you. I have just been thinking about... my past recently--I'm just worried we haven't seen the last of the Pasha. There is no way he would give up this easily.~
@2310 = ~Wait, please. I... I have to speak to you.~
@2311 = ~I mean I've been thinking about my past a lot recently, and I'm not sure we've seen the last of the Pasha. I'm not convinced and... it scares me.~
@2312 = ~We killed those he sent after you. That should send a message. A rational person would cut his losses.~
@2313 = ~He has no legal claim on you anymore, Fade. You've destroyed the contract. What can he do?~
@2314 = ~I'm not so sure, <CHARNAME>. The Pasha won't give up so easily. He believes I've made a fool of him, and he suffers such from no one.~
@2315 = ~(gather her into a warm embrace) I've thought as much, but hoped I was wrong.~
@2316 = ~(Her tail snakes up between you to wrap itself around an arm. She makes small sounds of contentment as she eases back against your chest) Really? I... I don't want this to be your problem <CHARNAME>. It's something I have to deal with--you've got enough going on to worry about as it is.~
@2317 = ~Fade, your problems *are* my problems. That's what being together is all about. If it happens, and I sincerely hope it doesn't... well, we'll sort it out. The Pasha has no claim to you, and I won't let him take you.~
@2318 = ~Please, stop worrying what *might* happen. We may all get eaten by a dragon tomorrow--we don't know! There's really no point in letting it eat at you like this.~
@2319 = ~What worries me more is that you are unhappy. (Kiss her neck) What would it take to make you happy again?~
@2320 = ~You could never do that <CHARNAME>--never. If anyone is adding to troubles it'll probably be me.~
@2321 = ~You're worried about the Pasha aren't you? We've dealt with his men, Fade. You'll be alright.~
@2322 = ~(gather her into a warm embrace) Your troubles are my troubles Fade. I'd have it no other way.~
@2323 = ~But I do worry. There's no guarantee Mallon will give the gold to the Pasha or that the contract he gave you is even valid. It looked real enough, but it could have been a fake. I just don't think he'd give up so easily.~
@2324 = ~We beat him once, we could do it again.~
@2325 = ~I won't let him take you again, Fade. I promise you that.~
@2326 = ~In case you missed it in my previous discussions with you, the Pasha is *not* a rational man. He thinks I've made a fool of him and now, so have you. I doubt he'll simply suffer such insults.~
@2327 = ~I really don't think it will be up to you, <CHARNAME>. If he decides to come after me again, there will be no choice.~
@2328 = ~I can't help it. If he decides to come after me again, there will be no choice in the matter, believe me.~
@2329 = ~(smile) You do know how to take a girl's mind off her troubles, I'll you give that.~
@2330 = ~(tilt her head gently upwards) Oh? You think this is distracting?~
@2331 = ~The future will bring what it will. I'd much rather enjoy the here and now.~
@2332 = ~(hug her to you and nuzzle her cheek) I'm at your command.~
@2333 = ~I know, <CHARNAME>. It's just... ~
@2334 = ~(let her continue)~
@2335 = ~(silence her with a kiss)~
@2336 = ~I believe you, <CHARNAME>. It's just... ~
@2337 = ~(You lower your lips to hers gently at first, but this soon gives way to a hungry probing. You feel her tail constricting around you as she reaches up to pull your head closer to hers)~
@2338 = ~(When you finally break free, it is obvious you have distracted Fade from her melancholy thoughts. She looks at you with eyes alight with desire and there is tightness low in your body)~
@2339 = ~You've really got to stop doing that to me, <CHARNAME>, but I take your point. Stop worrying about the past, and fearing the future.~
@2340 = ~(grin) In fact... I think I'm rather looking forward to our immediate future. (She pulls you closer to her and kisses you again)~
@2341 = ~Yes, sometimes that sentiment is appropriate. (grins) Although what *you* undoubtedly have on your mind will have to wait until later! I think we have to get going now, or we won't be popular!~
@2342 = ~Oh, really? (She turns to face you a wicked smile on her face) Well, let's just see how well you take orders later on... ~
@2343 = ~I... I couldn't bear it if you were injured because of me. I just couldn't... .~
@2344 = ~And I couldn't bear to have you taken away from me. I am a Child of Bhaal and if need be I will remind the Pasha of that, even if I have to bring his palace down around him to do it.~
@2345 = ~No more than I could bear to have you taken from me. Enough of this, we both have enough bad memories--let us make some good ones.~
@2346 = ~(sigh) Hearing you say that... that you'd come for me, no matter what... it makes me feel truly safe for the first time I can remember. Thank you, <CHARNAME>.~
@2347 = ~(grin) My thoughts exactly! Although maybe later, huh? I think we have to get going now, or we won't be popular!~

//LT58
@2348 = ~You know, it's funny how things have worked out. I sometimes wonder how things would have turned out if Keita had escaped... if she were still alive.~
@2349 = ~You really miss her, don't you?~
@2350 = ~Fade, you really have to stop torturing yourself over what happened to Keita.~
@2351 = ~I've wondered that myself. Would we have even met? I doubt it.~
@2352 = ~Yes, I do. She deserved to escape more that I did. She endured much, much more than me for much, much longer. It... it doesn't seem fair that I am here, enjoying myself, while she is dead.~
@2353 = ~You really have to stop torturing yourself this, Fade. Like I have said before, it wasn't your fault.~
@2354 = ~Unfortunately, these things happen. All you can do now is look to the future, and on what we have.~
@2355 = ~What are you saying? That you'd rather she was alive and that we had never met?~
@2356 = ~Fade, please, I don't want to keep going over this. It happened, and there was nothing you could do.~
@2357 = ~I... I can't help it, <CHARNAME>. I know I did everything in my power to keep her safe, but she still died. I look at myself now and wonder how different I would be as a person if she had survived.~
@2358 = ~Yes, I doubt it too. I expect Keita and I would have traveled further north, to Luskan, or to Waterdeep. I certainly wouldn't have become a Shadow Thief. We talked about it a lot--traveling around, helping people in the same situation as us. If only... if only she hadn't died on me.~
@2359 = ~So what you're basically saying is I should just get over it? Just forget her and concentrate solely on you? Act like she had never existed... like she never mattered?~
@2360 = ~Fade, I didn't mean it like that, and you know it!~
@2361 = ~Stop being so defensive! All I am saying is you can't keep dwelling on the past all the time.~
@2362 = ~No, of course not! Her memory should be honoured, but not to the expense of your future happiness.~
@2363 = ~Of course I would rather she was alive! I mean... of course I'm glad we've met and everything, but at the expense of someone's life? I... I can't help it <CHARNAME>, but sometimes I feel very guilty.~
@2364 = ~You can't keep focusing on the past like this. What happened, *happened*. Don't let it ruin what we have.~
@2365 = ~Don't be defensive, Fade--you know what I mean!~
@2366 = ~Keita wouldn't have wanted you to feel guilty about being happy, Fade. It's right to remember her, but not at the expense of your future happiness!~
@2367 = ~Oh, so I'm boring you now? Well, I'm sorry, <CHARNAME>! Would you prefer it if I just forgot her altogether then, and concentrated solely on you?~
@2368 = ~Do I? You're asking me to basically dismiss one of the most important people in my life. Alive or dead, Keita meant everything to me! I thought you at least would understand that.~
@2369 = ~Of course I understand that! I feel exactly the same way about Imoen.~
@2370 = ~Of course I understand! Her memory should be honoured, but not at the expense on your future happiness.~
@2371 = ~I'm NOT being defensive! I don't see that there is anything wrong with remembering you loved ones and feeling bad about the fact that they are *dead*.~
@2372 = ~And I'm not saying that there *is* anything wrong with remembering the dead! All I am saying is that you shouldn't sacrifice your future happiness by focusing on it all the time!~
@2373 = ~Please, stop dwelling on the past all the time. What happened, *happened*. Don't let it ruin what we have.~
@2374 = ~Maybe you forget, but I too have lost loved ones... many of us here have. And although we remember them every day of our lives, we don't let their memory get to us in the way that the memory of Keita gets to you!~
@2375 = ~<CHARNAME>, Keita is part of who I am! Without her, I certainly wouldn't be here today--and I don't think you understand that!~
@2376 = ~I do understand, Fade. I just don't want it to ruin what we have!~
@2377 = ~Always thinking of yourself, huh, <CHARNAME>? I... I've had enough of talking to you now. I need some time to myself to remember my dead friend.~
@2378 = ~Yes, but at least there's a good chance Imoen is still alive! There is still a good chance everything will be okay for the two of you. Not so for Keita and me!~
@2379 = ~I'm sorry, <CHARNAME>, but I think I need some time to myself now. Whether you like it or not, I need to think about my very *dead* friend.~
@2380 = ~But Imoen is alive! You *did* manage to rescue her--I never had the luxury!~
@2381 = ~Well, maybe I can't cope with these things as well as you can! I'm sorry, <CHARNAME>, but I think I need some time to myself now. Whether you like it or not, I need to think about my very *dead* friend.~

//LT60
@2382 = ~(She catches your arm and entwines her fingers around yours) Hi.~
@2383 = ~Hey, how are you? Have you calmed down now?~
@2384 = ~Fade, I never meant to upset you over Keita. I suppose I didn't realise everything is still so raw for you.~
@2385 = ~What do you want?~
@2386 = ~Yes. I'm sorry, <CHARNAME>. I realise now what you were trying to say to me, but I was in such a bleak mood... I shouldn't have taken it out on you.~
@2387 = ~You don't have to apologise. I'm just thankful you realise I wasn't trying to upset you.~
@2388 = ~I'm sorry too. I suppose I thought that after all this time, things wouldn't still be so raw for you. I didn't mean to upset you.~
@2389 = ~All I want is for you to be happy, Fade. I don't want you to forget Keita, just to stop punishing yourself over what happened.~
@2390 = ~I know you didn't. I just get a little... oversensitive about things occasionally, and I'm sorry. I really shouldn't take it out on you.~
@2391 = ~It's okay. I'm just thankful you realise I wasn't trying to upset you.~
@2392 = ~(smile) I suppose we inevitably hit out against those we are dearest to. I don't blame you.~
@2393 = ~(sigh) I suppose I deserve as much. I... I just want to say I'm sorry--again. I realise now what you were trying to say to me, and you're right. I shouldn't let Keita's death get to me so much. And I certainly shouldn't have taken it out on you. I'm sorry.~
@2394 = ~I know. And you're right, I do need to let go--to remember Keita as she was in life, not in death. She wouldn't want me to be dwelling on this. She would be pleased that I'm so happy with you. I... shouldn't feel guilty.~
@2395 = ~Letting go doesn't mean you have to forget her. Treasure her memory--don't use it as a weapon against yourself!~
@2396 = ~And I'm pleased you have realized that at last. You are allowed a little bit of happiness in your life!~
@2397 = ~What brought this about, anyway? Are you still concerned about the Pasha?~
@2398 = ~I'll try, <CHARNAME>. I realise now that all of this negativity does her memory no favours--it won't bring her back. I should be thankful for what I have now... and be thankful that I did at least have the chance to know her, even if it was cut short so cruelly.~
@2399 = ~I know nothing I can say will take away the pain of your loss, even after all these years, but please know that I am here for you. Treasure her memory--don't use it as a weapon against yourself!~
@2400 = ~Be thankful, but don't feel guilty about allowing yourself a little bit of happiness in your life. If Keita cared for you half as much as you obviously cared for her, she would never begrudge you that.~
@2401 = ~Yes, I suppose we do. You know, I actually blamed Keita for what happened for months afterwards? I thought her... selfish for leaving me. Then I realized I was being the selfish one, and that hurt.~
@2402 = ~Now I understand. I do need to let go and remember Keita as she was in life, not in death. She wouldn't want me to be dwelling on this. She would be pleased that I'm so happy with you. I... shouldn't feel guilty.~
@2403 = ~Fade, the way you felt after Keita's death was totally normal. I felt exactly the same after Gorion died. I still feel that way sometimes, but that's only natural. I would be a lot more concerned if it didn't bother you.~
@2404 = ~I'll try, <CHARNAME>, I really will. Thank you for understanding.~
@2405 = ~(smile) I think you qualify as a little more than just a *little* bit of happiness, <CHARNAME>.~
@2406 = ~Yes, I am. And in thinking about him, I inevitably started thinking about Keita. If anyone is to blame, it's that bastard.~
@2407 = ~Please, don't think about him. You're safe now, and entitled to a little bit of happiness as much as the next person.~
@2408 = ~And if I *ever* get to meet that bastard... ~
@2409 = ~You... you felt the same way after Gorion's death? I didn't know that. I thought it may have been because I am Fey'ri. We're not known for our compassion, but if that's not the case... thank you, <CHARNAME>. That is a great comfort to me.~
@2410 = ~I hope you never do. I can't risk losing someone else I love to him.~

//LT62
@2411 = ~I know I've asked you something like this before, <CHARNAME>, but do you ever think of the future?~
@2412 = ~What do you mean?~
@2413 = ~Of course I do. I'm always thinking about what is going to happen next.~
@2414 = ~Not much. So much has happened to me recently, I haven't given it a lot of thought.~
@2415 = ~Well... after all this. After you've sorted Irenicus out. What then?~
@2416 = ~Oh, that. No, I haven't given it much thought, to be honest with you.~
@2417 = ~I'm not entirely sure. It would be nice to leave the adventuring life behind, though... ~
@2418 = ~I expect I'll carry on seeking adventure. I can't ever see myself settling down.~
@2419 = ~So... what then? What do you see?~
@2420 = ~It would be nice to settle down, I suppose, leave the adventuring life behind. I quite fancy a little farm somewhere.~
@2421 = ~I'd like to think I'd still be adventuring. I can't ever see myself settling down.~
@2422 = ~I can understand that sentiment. I suppose with everything you've been through, *not* living on a purely day-to-day basis would seem pretty strange.~
@2423 = ~What are you suggesting, then? That you do our thinking for us? What do you want for the future?~
@2424 = ~Exactly. Although I suppose settling down would be nice... ~
@2425 = ~Well, I can't ever see myself ever abandoning the adventuring life and settling down. I don't think I'd do that very well.~
@2426 = ~Really? You'd like to leave the adventuring life? That does kind of surprise me.~
@2427 = ~Why should it? I quite fancy getting myself a little farm somewhere.~
@2428 = ~(grin) So you'd expect me to still be adventuring when I'm old and grey, huh? No, I don't think so. By that time, I think I'd like to be settled, with a tribe of grandchildren to tell my tales to.~
@2429 = ~I thought you'd say that. But do you ever just wish you could... leave it all behind and just live a simpler, more settled life?~
@2430 = ~No, it would drive me insane! Could you imagine it? Waking in the same bed everyday, doing the same chores day in day out... it would be so boring!~
@2431 = ~Maybe later--just not right now. I'd like to see more of Faerun before I ever think of settling down.~
@2432 = ~(laugh) A farm? For some reason, I can't see you feeding chickens, <CHARNAME>.~
@2433 = ~Why not? It would be nice: the two of us, with a little place of our own. Unless that's not what you want.~
@2434 = ~Yes, I suppose it does stretch the imagination a bit. So what do you see for us, then?~
@2435 = ~(grin) Well, if you're going to laugh at me... what do *you* want for the future?~
@2436 = ~Me? I'm not really sure. That's why I asked you. I... I suppose I just wondered if I had a place in your future.~
@2437 = ~Of course you do! I can't imagine a future without you... unless that's not what you want.~
@2438 = ~Who knows what the future may bring? Let's just enjoy what we have now, and worry about what happens next when it happens!~
@2439 = ~Grandchildren? But for that you need children.~
@2440 = ~What's wrong, Fade? Don't you want kids?~
@2441 = ~Fade, I think you're jumping ahead of yourself here. Who knows what the future may bring? Let's just enjoy what we have now, and worry about what comes next when it happens.~
@2442 = ~(sigh) Yes, after all the excitement, settling down would seem boring. But even if you did continue to adventure... would you want me with you?~
@2443 = ~Of course I would! I can't imagine a future without you... unless that's not what you want.~
@2444 = ~Well, you already know I would agree with you on that. I'd love to see more of Faerun. With you. If that's what you want.~
@2445 = ~Of course that's what I want! I can't imagine a future without you... unless that's not what you want.~
@2446 = ~(You hold her close, and she returns your embrace, her head on your shoulder. You both stand for a long moment enjoying the closeness till Fade moves back enough to look at you)~
@2447 = ~That's what I want. Wherever I go or whatever I do, so long as you're with me, I know I'll be happy... and safe.~
@2448 = ~And you'll never be bored. (drop your hands to her hips and tickle her)~
@2449 = ~And loved. (kiss her)~
@2450 = ~(grin) What do I see? I'd like to think that I'd see us. Together. For a long, long time.~
@2451 = ~I'm glad we agree! It would be nice to settle down someday, with a tribe of grandchildren to tell our tales to.~
@2452 = ~Of course I do! As long as that's what you want too.~
@2453 = ~Oh. Well, I suppose you're right. Let us live life for the now. (She smiles and kisses you lightly, pulling you closer to her)~
@2454 = ~(She looks slightly embarrassed) Well... maybe, one day. Although I'm not too sure I'd make such a great mother.~
@2455 = ~(She then laughs and cups your chin with her hand) But I fear we are getting ahead of ourselves! I suppose I just wondered... if I had a place in your future, that's all.~
@2456 = ~(She makes a small sound of surprise that quickly gives way to laughter that fills the air) Oh no, not with you. *Never* will I be bored.~
@2457 = ~(She slaps your hand away) Come on. We've got a ways to go yet, and you can use the time to think of how you'll cure my... boredom tonight.~
@2458 = ~(Your lips find hers as your hand slides up into her hair. The kiss is long and soft, your tongues slowly caressing each other's lips. When you finally pull back you are both wearing contented smiles) Now how could I forget that?~
@2459 = ~(She takes your hand in hers and gives you a wink) Come on, we have a ways to go yet. Besides, I think I may have a memory lapse tonight, and you can use the time to think of how you'll... remind me I'm loved.~

@2460 = ~(You awaken to the dulcet sounds of someone being sick out of the window) No... no more... there isn't anything left... urrggh... ~
@2461 = ~(whisper) Serve you right!~
@2462 = ~Are you alright?~
@2463 = ~What did I say last night? I've got no sympathy for you!~
@2464 = ~(Get up and go over to her) Awww... poor baby.~
@2465 = ~I know you're awake. Go and get me a glass of water and... oh no... uurrrghhh... ~
@2466 = ~Nope, can't hear you. Anyway, I'm asleep.~
@2467 = ~No... It feels like a pig shat in my head.~
@2468 = ~Nice mental picture, Fade. Thanks for that. You want anything?~
@2469 = ~Please, the last thing I need now is... ulp... (takes some deep breaths) ... no, no, I'm okay... a lecture! I feel terrible enough already.~
@2470 = ~(Get up and go over to her) Aww... poor baby. Come to <CHARNAME>.~
@2471 = ~So you're not going to want any breakfast either?~
@2472 = ~(grin) I know something that'll make you feel better... ~
@2473 = ~Oh, ha ha. Don't be so bloody sarcastic. I really do feel... oohh... quite... ulp... dreadfu... (She leans out of the window again to be sick)~
@2474 = ~(sigh) That's right, get it all up. Maybe next time you'll think twice before challenging some dwarves to a drinking competition, eh?~
@2475 = ~I can cope with blood and gore, but sick? Sorry, Fade, but you're on your own!~
@2476 = ~Bastard... It feels like a pig shat in my head.~
@2477 = ~To die now, painlessly. Uuurrrggg... I'm NEVER drinking again, ever! (She leans out of the window to be sick again)~
@2478 = ~No!~
@2479 = ~So, you don't want some lovely, crispy bacon, topped with a deliciously oozing runny egg, with yolk just dripping?~
@2480 = ~That's okay then, I can eat yours!~
@2481 = ~Well, if that's the case, I know something that'll make you feel better... ~
@2482 = ~And is this "something" the same "something" that you claim to be the miracle cure for all headaches, back pain and stomach cramps too?~
@2483 = ~Heh heh... yep! <CHARNAME>'s magic wand, cures what ails you!~
@2484 = ~Well, it would take your mind off being ill.~
@2485 = ~Yes... bloody dwarves... all their fault!~
@2486 = ~Hmmm. Because they held you down and just threw the drink down your throat, didn't they?~
@2487 = ~Yes, dear, of course it is.~
@2488 = ~Bloody coward. (sigh) Go on then. I'll be okay in a bit. Go, have some breakfast and get ready, I should be alright by then.~
@2489 = ~Bastard! (She throws up out of the window again) Please... if you're going to talk about food, just bugger off and do it elsewhere. I don't think I can cope.~
@2490 = ~(sigh) Okay, I was only teasing. Maybe next time you'll think *twice* before challenging some dwarves to a drinking competition, eh?~
@2491 = ~Okay, okay, I'll go! Just make sure you're alright to travel in a bit. We can't stop here all day.~
@2492 = ~Yes, you can eat mine. Go on, off you go. I'll be okay in a bit. Go, have some breakfast and get ready, I should be alright by then.~
@2493 = ~You just don't give up, do you?! <CHARNAME>, believe me, that is the *last* thing on my mind at the moment. Anyway, there's a very good chance I'd be sick on you, and I don't think you'd appreciate that.~
@2494 = ~(nuzzle the back of her neck) Sure I can't change your mind?~
@2495 = ~Eww... maybe you do have a point. Perhaps I'll go and get myself something to eat instead.~
@2496 = ~No it wouldn't! I just want to crawl into bed and die, not crawl into bed and be jumped by you! (grin) Well, not this time, anyway.~
@2497 = ~Ahhh. Maybe later then?~
@2498 = ~Well, at least I got a smile out of you. Perhaps I'll go get myself something to eat and see you later?~
@2499 = ~Oh, I wondered when you'd say that. Okay, okay, I've only got myself to blame! Still, bloody dwarves... Look, why don't you go and get ready and get yourself something to eat? I should be okay by then. Just get me a glass of water!~
@2500 = ~Oh, don't be so insufferably agreeable, <CHARNAME>. Go on, make yourself useful. Go and get me a glass of water, then go and get ready and get yourself something to eat. I should be okay by then.~
@2501 = ~Yes, yes, yes, point taken. Get me a glass of water, then go and get ready and get yourself something to eat. I should be okay by then.~
@2502 = ~(laugh) You're incorrigible! No, you can't change my mind. Go on, my horny champion. Go and get me a glass of water, then go and get ready and get yourself something to eat. I should be okay by then.~
@2503 = ~Yes, that's a good idea. Go and get ready and get yourself something to eat. I should be okay by then.~
@2504 = ~Okay, <CHARNAME>... maybe later. Now go and get me a glass of water, then go and get ready and get yourself something to eat. I should be okay by then.~

@2505 = ~I must say, I still cannot believe that <CHARNAME> even allowed you to join us, Fade. Let it be known that I shall never trust you, and whilst you travel with us, I shall always be watching you.~
@2506 = ~*Always* be watching me, Anomen? I'm sure I could have you arrested for that.~
@2507 = ~I suppose I should have expected such a response from one of your kind. Never did I think I would have to travel with a Shadow Thief!~
@2508 = ~Well, now, that's unfortunate, isn't it? Especially since <CHARNAME>'s joined our ranks and everything. I would say you're outnumbered, Anomen.~
@2509 = ~Well, <CHARNAME > is the one calling the shots here, not you, so I think you can just toddle off back to your position and concentrate on being righteous, while the rest of us have some fun.~

@2510 = ~Have you ever travelled to Sigil?~
@2511 = ~No... never.~
@2512 = ~You surprise me, magpie! I know of your history--the Hellgate Saga is indeed an interesting one--but do the Planes not call to you?~
@2513 = ~Not really. Since the only other Plane I have had contact with is the Abyss, it hasn't done anything to whet my appetite to visit others.~
@2514 = ~But Sigil is a great city. Cruel, but exhilarating; brutal, but beautiful. Great heroes and villains walk its crooked streets, and there is adventure to be found at every turn. Ahhh... the Primes think they know of diversity and excitement, but compared to Sigil, there is nothing but routine and the mundane.~
@2515 = ~Well, if Sigil is so great, why are you here?~
@2516 = ~Discovery and exploration has her claws in this humble sparrow, and for all that Sigil has to recommend it, how else can I experience what the Prime has to offer? One day I will return... but until then, I shall travel.~

@2517 = ~What does it feel like to have faith?~
@2518 = ~What kind of question is that to ask anyone, Fade?~
@2519 = ~Well, you are a paladin and all... I just thought you would be the best person to ask.~
@2520 = ~I suppose I am as good as any, but it's still a surprising question. Are you saying you have no faith at all--in anything? I thought that even... thieves... had their own deities.~
@2521 = ~Come now, Keldorn. Thief I may be, but we're not all bad.~
@2522 = ~Please, forgive an old paladin for his even older misconceptions and prejudices. I know you are good of heart, if not necessarily of deed.~
@2523 = ~(grin) How could I not forgive you? But still... back to my question.~
@2524 = ~Faith... let me see... it is hard to explain. For me, it is like having a guiding light--Torm shows me the way. He protects me, and my family. I know I am safe in his care, so I trust him implicitly. I do not flounder under his tutelage; my life has purpose.~
@2525 = ~That sounds like a... nice way to live. But what if you come into conflict with him? Would Torm put up with that?~
@2526 = ~And why would I come into conflict with my God? It would be like conflicting with myself.~
@2527 = ~Fade, I fear I am trying to explain something to you that is very personal to each individual. I hope that you do one day gain a faith... something that gives you something to believe in.~
@2528 = ~You know, you're totally different from what I imagined a paladin would be like. I had thought them all stuffy, meddling, over-pious do-gooders... but you're not.~

@2529 = ~Get out of my way, rich kid.~
@2530 = ~What? I wasn't anywhere near you!~
@2531 = ~I can see you, and that's enough for me.~
@2532 = ~What is your problem with me, Fade? I don't see you being this beastly to anyone else.~
@2533 = ~My "problem" with you is that you have no idea of what you're talking about. If I have to hear about how you "help the needy" one more time, I'm going to be sick.~
@2534 = ~And what is wrong with that? Maybe you don't realise--or maybe you just don't care--but they need all the help I can give them!~
@2535 = ~Oh? Really? So how did your lounging around in your huge castle while they toiled in the fields to ensure there was food on your table help them, exactly? By giving them employment?~
@2536 = ~I cannot help it if I was born privileged! I have never been cruel to any of the castles servants. I have always treated them with respect, and spared a coin when I could.~
@2537 = ~A right little Ilmater, aren't you? Ever thought about giving them enough so they didn't have to slave for you anymore? No, I didn't think so. Just... go away.~

@2538 = ~I can't help but feel that we have got off on the wrong foot. I know about your causes, and I believe in them too! I just wish you would give me a chance.~
@2539 = ~A chance? I don't think so. Live in the gutter for a month, and then we'll speak. Until then, you have no clue what real suffering is about, Nalia... none at all.~

@2540 = ~You there! Yes, you--slave girl! Come here and rub my feet.~
@2541 = ~Are you talking to *me*?~
@2542 = ~(Deaf as well as stupid, I see) Yes, of course I am! Who else do you think I refer to? Now get to it.~
@2543 = ~How dare you! You demand I rub your feet--how about I cut them off?!~
@2544 = ~Bah! What's the point of having servants if they won't do as they're told?~

@2545 = ~So what made you turn your life as a sneak into a spell thrower?~
@2546 = ~(grin) I'm not sure. Shiny things are nice, but being able to manipulate raw arcane power... that's something else!~
@2547 = ~I suppose so, although it's been a long time since I cast any spells.~
@2548 = ~You were a spell caster once? What happened?~
@2549 = ~I lost my powers. I had a certain amount of innate magical power. My tutors tried to teach me how to use it properly, but I really couldn't be arsed. (sigh) Then I lost it. I kind of regret it.~
@2550 = ~So... how did you lose your powers? Did you just wake up one morning and find them gone?~
@2551 = ~No, I lost them gradually. (sigh) You... you know I was a slave? Well, a slave with magical powers doesn't make a good slave. I was forced to wear manacles that suppressed my magic. Whether it was the years of not using it, or whether the manacles themselves somehow sucked the magic right out of me, I don't know. Still--too late for regrets. We are what life makes us... and there's nothing we can do about it!~

@2552 = ~What was it like, growing up with <CHARNAME>? Were you as bad as <PRO_HESHE> likes to make out?~
@2553 = ~Me? The bad one? Hardly! <PRO_HESHE> was always blaming me for everything, getting me into trouble, saying I was the one who kept stealing the cookies, that I was the one who distracted <PRO_HIMHER> from <PRO_HISHER> chores and studies... (grin)~
@2554 = ~(wink) Ahhh. I guessed that might be the case.~
@2555 = ~You'd never know from that innocent little expression, would you?~
@2556 = ~So... stealing cookies, right? How often did you manage that?~
@2557 = ~A lot more times that I would care to admit, Fade. Well, in the presence of <CHARNAME>, anyway!~

@2558 = ~That's some mighty shiny armour you're wearing, Anomen.~
@2559 = ~Well, it doesn't do oneself any favours to look a disgrace, does it?~
@2560 = ~No, it doesn't. Although I do suppose people may wonder when you get the time to polish it. Considering all the heroic things you've done, I'm surprised you even have the time to sit down, let alone polish your helmet until it gleams... (flutters her eyelashes at Anomen)~
@2561 = ~What?!~
@2562 = ~Well... all that rubbing? It takes time! No wonder you've got such a nice, strong right arm. (grin)~
@2563 = ~Why must you bring down everything I say to the basest of levels? I... I tire of talking to you, fiendling. Leave me be!~

@2564 = ~So, little Shadow Thief! We are working together.~
@2565 = ~No, I don't think we are. We are simply helping out the same person.~
@2566 = ~What is that? Surely you do not share Renal's disdain? We should work together!~
@2567 = ~My Shadow Master warned me of you, thieving on our patch without the backing of the guild. How do we know you aren't a spy for the other guild?~
@2568 = ~You wound me! I am but an honest thief; never have I plotted against the Shadow Thieves, nor against the Shadow Master. I was simply trying to survive.~
@2569 = ~Honest thief? A bit of an oxymoron... remember who you are speaking to! But I'm watching you, Yoshimo. Any treachery, and you *will* be dealt with.~

@2570 = ~I... I just wanted to say that I was very sorry to hear about your capture and subsequent incarceration, Aerie.~
@2571 = ~Wh-what? Why should you care? I mean... I wouldn't have thought you would even have considered it.~
@2572 = ~Well, I have, and if you ever need... you know... someone to talk to about it... well, you know where I am.~
@2573 = ~Th-thank you Fade. Although I don't know if you could be of any help to me.~
@2574 = ~You'd be surprised, Aerie--I think we have more in common than you could ever imagine.~

@2575 = ~You know, you remind me a lot of me sometimes, Viconia.~
@2576 = ~I seriously doubt that, naut kleel uss. You come from the gutter. I do not. Let us leave it at that.~
@2577 = ~No... you may not like it, but we have a lot in common. (smiles sweetly) I used to be an unpleasant, bitter old bitch too, you know.~
@2578 = ~Indeed? Well I have *never* been a gutter whore, so I fail to see any similarities between us. Bwael tangi, Fade... xun naut vrine'winith ulu sevir ussta llanath. That is to say--Good day... do not hesitate to leave my presence.~

@2579 = ~Why do you persist in keeping that... protrusion, Fade?~
@2580 = ~Protrusion? You mean my tail? Well, it's not like I can just get rid of it--it's part of me!~
@2581 = ~You could have cut it off. I could easily arrange that for you. It wouldn't hurt... much.~
@2582 = ~Get away, Viconia! I don't *want* to lose my tail! It's part of who I am.~
@2583 = ~Hmmm? Part of who you are? I suppose there is some truth in that statement. Many animals have tails... so why shouldn't you?~

@2584 = ~Why so glum, chum?~
@2585 = ~Fade, if you are going to be insufferably perky, can you do it to someone else? I am in no mood for it today.~
@2586 = ~(sigh) Come on, Valygar, there's no need to be so sour. Just a smile--one small smile. Is that so hard?~
@2587 = ~Yes, it is. Please, just leave me be.~
@2588 = ~Come on... smile... ~
@2589 = ~Fade... ~
@2590 = ~Smile... let's see those lovely lips of yours in something other than a frown... ~
@2591 = ~Pardon?~
@2592 = ~(grin) See what depths I will subject myself to? Or am I going to have to sink even lower and tickle you too?~

//LT64
@2593 = ~(She snakes an arm around your waist and grins at you. She then winks, and you feel her roving hand travel south, looking for gaps in your armour) I wonder what we have in here...~
@2594 = ~(grin) You know damn well what's in there. Pack it in!~
@2595 = ~(mock-growl) Minx.~
@2596 = ~Fade, what are you doing?!~
@2597 = ~Oi, stop that!~
@2598 = ~(She flutters her eyelashes at you playfully as her hand continues its roving) Oh come on, <CHARNAME>... where's your sense of adventure?~
@2599 = ~(whisper) I said pack it in!~
@2600 = ~Fade, not with everyone else around! We might get caught.~
@2601 = ~Adventure? So what are you suggesting? That we just get it on here and now, in front of everyone?~
@2602 = ~(snicker) So... what do you think? (She bites her bottom lip, looking up at you expectantly)~
@2603 = ~No... not here, not now. Later on, okay?~
@2604 = ~What? Right here, in front of everyone?~
@2605 = ~(grin) Isn't it obvious?~
@2606 = ~Yes, you little minx!~
@2607 = ~Come on, let's just stop for a bit. (Her grin widens*) I'll make it worth your while...~
@2608 = ~I said stop it and I mean stop it!~
@2609 = ~I know. (whisper) But that's what makes it all the more exciting...~
@2610 = ~Not for me it doesn't! Maybe later, when we're alone, okay?~
@2611 = ~Exciting? Really?~
@2612 = ~You really are a terrible influence on me, you know.~
@2613 = ~Of course not! We could just stop for a bit and find somewhere a little more secluded.~
@2614 = ~But we might still get caught!~
@2615 = ~(She looks slightly disappointed and rather frustrated) Alright... (grin) But you'd better have something quite spectacular in mind, okay?~
@2616 = ~(She moves her hand and hugs your arm) I'm sorry... I didn't mean to embarrass you.~
@2617 = ~(She nods, grinning wickedly) Now you just go and tell everyone we're taking a break, and I'll meet *you* over there. (She points to a secluded spot)~
@2618 = ~No problem!~
@2619 = ~Fade, I didn't mean that as an invitation. I can't do this here and now. Maybe later on, okay?~
@2620 = ~(She grins wickedly) I aim to please,  <CHARNAME>. Now you just go and tell everyone we're taking a break, and I'll meet *you* over there. (She points to a secluded spot)~
@2621 = ~(As you turn to leave, she grabs your arm and whispers in your ear) But don't take too long, or I may be... forced to start without you. (wink)~

//LT66
@2622 = ~That is it. I'm free. No longer just someone's lackey... and I have you to thank for it all, <CHARNAME>! I... I thought I knew what happiness was before, but now I know it was all just an illusion, because this is true happiness. You are true happiness.~
@2623 = ~(say nothing, just hold her close to you)~
@2624 = ~(smile) You're making me blush.~
@2625 = ~No, I'm not true happiness. The knowledge that you are able to do what you want from now on is true happiness. Being true to yourself is real happiness. I'm just glad I was able to help you.~
@2626 = ~(She holds you tightly back, and you soon realise from the trembling in her shoulders that she is crying)~
@2627 = ~Fade, come now... why are you upset? This is a happy time, not crying time!~
@2628 = ~You don't need to cry, sweetheart. Everything has worked out fine.~
@2629 = ~Don't be so melodramatic, Fade. Come on, we're drawing a crowd! Let's just... you know... get on with what we have to do.~
@2630 = ~It's true, though. I joined up with you to achieve one goal, and you've allowed me to achieve so much more, more than I ever dreamed possible. I... I don't think there is anything I can do to ever repay you. I... you... it's just...~
@2631 = ~(She trails off, obviously lost for words)~
@2632 = ~Us being together is not a transaction, Fade! Think of all the things you've done for me in the past! And of the things you are bound to do for me... for us... in the future. I wouldn't have it any other way.~
@2633 = ~You're absolutely hopeless! I've done these things because I love you, not to gain something from you! We're a partnership, kid... and a bloody fine one too.~
@2634 = ~(laugh) Always so modest! But you know I speak the truth. I joined up with you to achieve one goal, and you've allowed me to achieve so much more, more than I ever dreamed possible. I... I don't think there is anything I can do to ever repay you. I... you... it's just...~
